                     "meta_value": {
                        "__cdata": "a:18:{i:1582639591910;s:1385:\"<a href=\"http://coolice.legis.iowa.gov/cool-ice/default.asp?category=billinfo&amp;service=iowacode&amp;input=252J\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>Iowa Code Chapter 252J</b></a> (broken link) provides for the enforcement of child support obligations through the suspension, revocation, non-issuance, or non-renewal of a driver\'\'s license, motor vehicle registrations, recreational licenses, business or industry licenses, or professional or occupational licenses.\n\nThe goal of the license sanction process is to encourage payors to pay their child support rather than risk losing their license. The process provides the payor with many opportunities to pay the support owed and avoid the loss of licenses. At various points in the process, the payor may request a conference with CSRU to enter into a payment agreement or to provide verification of a qualifying exemption from the process.\n\nIf the payor is unable to resolve the situation administratively with CSRU, the payor may request a district court hearing.\n\nThe LISAN process is centralized at EPICS, effective July 7, 2014.\n\nEPICS staff complete all actions/steps in the process except for:\n<ul>\n \t<li>In-Person Conferences</li>\n \t<li>District Court hearings</li>\n</ul>\nEPICS staff are assigned to caseloads by an alpha split. This assists payors with multiple cases so they have one LISAN worker for all cases.\";i:1582639592335;s:8557:\"<b>EPICS MISSION STATEMENT</b>\n\nProvide the highest quality of Customer Service for the everyday life of those we serve; through education and enforcement. As a result, our focus is on strengthening and increasing collections!\n\n<b>EPICS: History and Services</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>EPICS stands for Employers Partnering in Child Support.</li>\n \t<li>The unit opened in 1999 and its original focus was serving as a one-stop shop for employers.</li>\n \t<li>The unit is a single point of contact for over 193,000 Iowa employers who contact EPICS to obtain answers to their questions about child support.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS processes income withholding orders which produce over 75% of the annual collections.</li>\n \t<li>Over the years EPICS has expanded its work and now provides specialized enforcement services for income withholding, medical, levy, license sanction and debtor offsets.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>URGENT REFERRALS FROM CSRU FIELD TO EPICS</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>DEFINITION URGENT REFFERALS TO EPICS:\n\nMake an URGENT referral <b>ONLY</b> when an action MUST be taken on the same day. If the referral is received by 3:00 pm it will be worked the same day. URGENT referrals received after 3:00 pm will be processed on the same day if at all possible. Otherwise, processing occurs on the following business day.\n\nAn URGENT referral can be related to <b>any</b> of the EPICS processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>INSTRUCTIONS FOR URGENT REFERRALS</b>\n\n1. Click on Urgent Referrals to EPICS\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/1stBox.png\" />\n\n2. Then, click on the Items tab\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/2ndBox.png\" />\n- Select New Item\n\n3. Complete the referral form.\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/3rdBox.png\" />\n\n<b>Case Number:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Required field</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Type of Referral:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Required field</li>\n \t<li>Only one type of referral can be selected</li>\n \t<li>If the referral is related to LISAN, select LISAN</li>\n \t<li>If the referral is related to <b>anything</b> else, select URGENT</li>\n</ul>\n<b>EPICS LISAN Wkr ID:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Whenever the referral is regarding LISAN, you <b>must</b> enter the SIGNATURE ID shown on the LISAN screen. This assures the referral is routed and processed timely.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Comments:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Not a required field</li>\n \t<li>You can enter any additional comments you have in this field such as: special instructions or the name of a Specialty Employer.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Date Created:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Defaults to current date – no entry required These are the only fields that need to be completed by the CSRU worker as EPICS will complete the remaining fields.</li>\n</ul>\n4. Click on SAVE and the referral is submitted.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>NON-URGENT REFERRALS FROM CSRU FIELD TO EPICS</b>\n\nDEFINITION NON-URGENT REFFERALS TO EPICS\n\nA NON-URGENT referral is made when an action is not needed the same date. This form is used for routine referrals related to any of EPICS processes. These are processed within 2 working days and should be used for all actions/responses that are not urgent.\n\n<b>INSTRUCTIONS FOR NON-URGENT REFERRALS</b>\n\n1. Click on Non-Urgent Referrals to EPICS\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/Box1.png\" />\n\n2. Then, click on the Items tab\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/2ndBox.png\" />\n- Select New Item\n\n3. Complete the referral form.\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/Box3.png\" />\n\n<b>Referral Type:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Required field</li>\n \t<li>EPICS-select this for routine referrals for EPICS Processes and also for Specialty Employer referrals</li>\n \t<li>DNR-select only for DNR Withdrawals</li>\n \t<li>LISAN-select only for LISAN related referrals</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Specialty Employer:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Specialty employers are: DFAS/VA, IWD (for UIB referrals), and SSA. Specific EPICS staff work with each of these specialty employers. Be sure to indicate which specialty employer the referral is for to assure referrals are routed to the appropriate worker to be processed.</li>\n</ul>\nLISAN EPICS Worker ID:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Whenever the referral is regarding LISAN, you <b>must</b> enter the SIGNATURE ID shown on the LISAN screen. This assures the referral is routed and processed timely.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Date Created:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Defaults to current date – no entry required</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Case Number:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Required field</li>\n</ul>\n4. Click on SAVE and the referral is submitted.\n\n<b>SPECIALTY EMPLOYERS</b>\n\nSpecialty employers are: DFAS/VA, IWD (for UIB referrals), and SSA. Specific EPICS staff work with each of these specialty employers. Be sure to indicate which specialty employer the referral is for to assure referrals are routed to the appropriate worker to be processed.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>REFERRAL GUIDES: WHEN REFERRALS SHOULD BE MADE FROM EPICS TO CSRU</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20Field/IWO%20Referrals%20to%20Field%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" /> IWO</a></li>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20Field/MEDICAL%20Referrals%20to%20CSRU%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" /> MEDICAL</a></li>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20Field/LISAN%20Referrals%20to%20Field%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" /> LISAN</a></li>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20Field/LEVY%20Referrals%20to%20CSRU%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" /> LEVY</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>REFERRAL GUIDES: WHEN REFERRALS SHOULD BE MADE FROM CSRU TO EPICS</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20EPICS/IWO%20Referrals%20to%20EPICS%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" />IWO</a></li>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20EPICS/MEDICAL%20Referrals%20to%20EPICS%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" />MEDICAL</a></li>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20EPICS/LISAN%20Referrals%20to%20EPICS%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" />LISAN</a></li>\n \t<li><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/EPICS%20Referrals/Guides/To%20EPICS/LEVY%20Referrals%20to%20EPICS%20Guide.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" />LEVY</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>QUICK LINKS to MAKE a REFERRAL to EPICS</b>\n\nLINKS to SHAREPOINT REFERRALS and EPICS LISAN WORKER BREAKDOWN\n<ul>\n \t<li>LINK TO SharePoint site to make <a href=\"http://dhssp/csr/field/EPICSref/Lists/URGENTSpecialty%20Employer%20Referral/AllItems.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/sharepoint.png\" /> URGENT CSRU FIELD REFERRALS to EPICS</b></a></li>\n \t<li>LINK TO SharePoint site to make <a href=\"http://dhssp/csr/field/EPICSref/Lists/Referrals%20to%20EPICS/AllItems.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/sharepoint.png\" /> NON-URGENT CSRU FIELD REFERRALS to EPICS</b></a></li>\n \t<li>LINK TO <a href=\"http://dhssp/csr/Central/epics/LISAN%20Training%20Documents/EPICS%20LISAN%20Caseload%20Assignment.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> EPICS LISAN WORKER ALPHA SPLIT</b></a></li>\n</ul>\";i:1582639592687;s:422:\"<a href=\"http://165.206.129.165/search?q=cache:Y4Sp1s_9zMsJ:intra.dhs.state.ia.us/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN,%2520Admin%2520Levy,%2520Credit/Contents/LISAN/Customer%2520Service/Cover.htm+LISAN+customer+&amp;access=p&amp;output=xml_no_dtd&amp;site=default_collection&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;client=csru_frontend&amp;proxystylesheet=csru_frontend&amp;oe=ISO-8859-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>(broken google link)</b></a>\";i:1582639593015;s:2666:\"See <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Case Selection, <i>ICAR Case Selection Criteria</i></b>.\n\n<b>ICAR Case Selection</b>\n\nICAR selects cases for license sanction based on certain criteria. The license sanction case selection program runs the weekend after the last working day of the month.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Bypassing Case Selection</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Screens Used in License Sanction Process, <i>CASESTAT</i> Screen</b>\n\nThe LISAN process should be bypassed in the following situations:\n<ul>\n \t<li>CSRU holds an Administrative Enforcement Conference (AEC) <b>and</b> the payor enters into an AEC payment agreement</li>\n \t<li>Current support obligation suspended due to change of custody AND\n<ul>\n \t<li>Obligation is suspended for all children covered by the order</li>\n \t<li>Child(ren) is a minor</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li>Payee is deceased and child(ren) are residing with the payor</li>\n \t<li>SRO/SRS determine LISAN is not an appropriate enforcement action</li>\n \t<li style=\"color: red;\">Case has been referred to the attorney for a contempt action</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>When LISAN had NOT already selected:</b>\n\n<i>CSRU</i> enters the bypass on the CASESTAT screen.\n\n<b>When LISAN is currently active:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>CSRU</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Review the case and narrate whether LISAN continues to be an appropriate enforcement action.</li>\n \t<li>Process end LISAN and enter the bypass on the CASESTAT screen when a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance (Form 470-3274)</i> is <b>NOT</b> in effect.</li>\n \t<li>When a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> <b>IS</b> in effect and LISAN is no longer appropriate, send an EPICS referral. Enter a bypass on the CASESTAT screen <b>after</b> EPICS has issued the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance (Form 470-3275)</i> and has process ended the LISAN screen.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li>EPICS\n<ul>\n \t<li>Issue the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance (Form 470-3275)</i> upon receiving a CSRU referral.</li>\n \t<li>Process end the LISAN screen (CSRU enters bypass; see above)</li>\n \t<li>Calendar Flags LISAN 47 and 48 will issue to the worker ID entering the bypass. The worker entering the bypass is responsible for updating or canceling the bypass</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\";i:1582639593333;s:1870:\"<b>Screening for an Exemption and Verification</b>\n\nUnder certain circumstances, an payor is exempt from the license sanction process.\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Exemption from the License Sanction Process</b>.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Recording a valid exemption</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Exemption from the License Sanction Process, <i>Recording a Valid Exemption</i></b>.\n\n<b style=\"color: red;\">Recommended Time Frames</b> - If no expiration date is entered, ICAR defaults to one year. Recommended time frames for exemptions are as follows:\n\n[ninja_tables id=\"930\"]\n\nIf the payor provides a physician’s statement indicating the disability is total/permanent, EPICS will set the exemption period for one year and send a referral to CSRU to review case closure criteria.\n<p style=\"color: red;\">EPICS will make a CSRU referral when the exemption period expires.</p>\n<p style=\"color: red;\">CSRU will review the case for the next appropriate action.</p>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Deleting or Changing an Exemption</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Exemption from the License Sanction Process, <i>Deleting or Changing an Exemption</i>.</b>\n\nYou may want to delete or change the exemption date when you determine that the exemption expired or you receive verification that the exemption is ongoing.\";i:1582639593702;s:3361:\"See the <b><i>Notice to Payor</i></b> section of <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G-App.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>License Sanction Appendix</b>\n\nSee the <b><i>Sending the Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i></b> section of <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>\n\n<hr />\n\nThe Official Notice of Potential License Sanction (470-3278) is mailed in an envelope with EPICS return address. A copy of the notice is loaded to PODS as part of the batch processing.\n\n<b>EPICS will receive any notices from the USPS which are undeliverable.</b>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Return Mail Processing (EPICS)</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> mails all LISAN forms to payors/payees in envelopes with EPICS return address and processes return mail as follows:\n\n<b>USPS Provides a New Address:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>Update ICAR with the new address information</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</li>\n \t<li>Update LISAN screen</li>\n \t<li>Regenerate notice prior to re-mailing</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Issue Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li>Wait 1 day and then update payor\'\'s address and re-issue the Certificate of Noncompliance</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>All other forms</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Re-mail to payor/payee</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<b>USPS Does Not Provide a New Address</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Remove invalid address from ICAR</li>\n \t<li>Complete location searches on the following on-line resources:\n<ul>\n \t<li>ICON</li>\n \t<li>IABC/ELIAS</li>\n \t<li>VRT</li>\n \t<li>LOCDB</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li>Review any unverified/hidden addresses on ADDVER (ADDVERSUM). Update if appropriate.</li>\n \t<li><b>Address is Located</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Update LISAN screen</li>\n \t<li>Regenerate notice prior to re-mailing</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Issue Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li>Wait 1 day and then update payor\'\'s address and re-issue the Certificate of Noncompliance</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>All other forms</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Re-mail to payor/payee</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><b>No Address is Located</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Update LISAN screen</li>\n \t<li>Make a referral to the office assigned to the case for additional location</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Do NOT issue a Withdrawal of Noncompliance as only required to send to the last known address</li>\n \t<li>Make a referral to the office assigned to the case for additional location</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>All other forms</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Make a referral to the office assigned to the case for additional location</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\";i:1582639594039;s:11833:\"<b>Request for Conference</b>\n\nA payor must request a conference in writing.\n\nA payor\'\'s ROI may not request a conference on behalf of the payor. An ROI (release of information) only allows an authorized person to receive the same information as the case party who gives the authorization. It does not allow someone to act on behalf of a case party.\n\n<b>Phone Conference</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> processes all requests for conference as a phone conference unless the payor specifically requests an in-person conference.\n\nWhen CSRU receives a request for conference, send it to EPICS through PODS by indexing the request to the worker ID shown in the SIGNATURE ID field on the LISAN screen.\n\n<b>In-Person Conference</b>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> processes all requests for in-person conferences.\n\nWhen EPICS receives a request for conference send it to CSRU through PODS by indexing the request to the worker ID shown on the CASE screen.\n\nIf a payor comes to CSRU when a phone conference has been scheduled, CSRU staff should accompany the payor to an interview room and place a call to EPICS at the scheduled time so the conference can be held as scheduled.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Scheduling the Conference</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>\n\n, License Sanction Conference, <i>Scheduling the Conference</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>If you have already issued the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, schedule the conference as soon as possible within the 10- to 30-day timeframe. This may help prevent the payor\'\'s license from being sanctioned if you later determine a license sanction should not be pursued.</li>\n \t<li>If you have not already issued the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, do not issue it until after the conference - if the results of the conference are to issue the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Preparing for the Conference</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, License Sanction Conference, <i>Preparing for the Conference</i>\n\nReview financial information and complete a guideline calculation prior to the scheduled conference.\n\nFollow the flowchart <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/REVIEWING%20FINANCIAL%20INFORMATION-flowchart[1].pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b> <img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Reviewing Financial Information</b></a> when determining what income information to use in the calculation.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Requesting Financial Statements</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/REVIEWING%20FINANCIAL%20INFORMATION-flowchart[1].pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b> <img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, License Sanction Conference, <i>Requesting Financial Statements from the Payor and Payee</i>\n\nA copy of <b>blank</b> financial statements should NOT be put in PODS.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Calculating the Payment - Agreement Amount</b>\n\nSee Title <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b> <img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>License Sanction Conference, Calculating the Payment Agreement Amount</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/REVIEWING%20FINANCIAL%20INFORMATION-flowchart[1].pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Reviewing Financial Information flowchart</b></a>\n\n<b>Payor Fails to Return Financial Statement</b>\n\nIf the payor’s occupation is known, complete the guidelines calculation using occupational wage.\n\nIf the payor’s occupation is unknown use CSRU median income.\n\nHold the conference and offer the payor a LISAN payment agreement. If the payor does not agree an alternate option is to enter into an AEC payment agreement for 75% of the IWO rate. For more information on entering into an AEC agreement see AEC AGREEMENT IN LIEU OF LISAN.\n\nWhen the payor does not agree to either option, request additional financial information and re-schedule the conference.\n\nEXCEPTION: When the payor is self-employed tax returns and appropriate schedules or other documentation of business income &amp; expenses are required.\n\n<b>Payor Returns Financial Statement</b>\n\n<b>Reports $0 income/unemployed</b>\n\nWhen the payor reports $0 income/unemployed and is receiving FA or MA calculate the guidelines using $0 income as reported on the financial statement.\n\nWhen the payor is not receiving FA or MA review on-line sources for income/assets. Use the <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/Conference%20Guide.docx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" /> Conference Desk Aid</b></a> to guide your review.\n\nCompare information from your review to the financial statement. If the financial statement is questionable determine probing questions to ask during the conference and what additional verification to request. The <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/Conference%20Guide.docx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> LISAN Conference Guide</b></a> provides examples of probing questions.\n\nThe payor may provide additional information regarding income during the conference. Clearly document this information in the case narrative. A guideline calculation may be done using this verbal information.\n\n<b>Reports Income-Not self-employed</b>\n\nWhen the payor reports income that is not from self-employment review on-line sources for income/assets. Use the <a href=\"http://dhssp/csr/Central/epics/_layouts/xlviewer.aspx?id=/csr/Central/epics/LISAN%20BPH/CONFERENCE%20DESK%20AID.xlsm&amp;Source=http%3A%2F%2Fdhssp%2Fcsr%2FCentral%2Fepics%2FLISAN%2520BPH%2FForms%2FAllItems%2Easpx%3FPaged%3DTRUE%26p%5FSortBehavior%3D0%26p%5FFileLeafRef%3D30%252dContinuing%2520License%2520Sanction%2520on%2520Cases%2520When%2520Pursuing%2520an%252edocx%26p%5FID%3D30%26PageFirstRow%3D31%26%26View%3D%7B2C446DF3%2DB6AC%2D43E5%2D9F1D%2DA186F2A53C2C%7D&amp;DefaultItemOpen=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/excel.png\" /> Conference Desk Aid</b></a> to guide your review.\n\nCompare information from your review to the financial statement. If the financial statement is questionable determine probing questions to ask during the conference and what additional verification to request. The <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/Conference%20Guide.docx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> LISAN Conference Guide</b></a> provides examples of probing questions.\n\nThe payor may provide additional information regarding income during the conference. Clearly document this information in the case narrative. A guideline calculation may be done using this verbal information.\n\n<b>Reports self-employed</b>\n\nA guideline calculation can only be completed when the payor has provided copies of tax returns and appropriate schedules or other documentation of business income &amp; expenses.\n\nIf the payor has not provided all necessary information do not complete a guideline calculation prior to the conference. At the conference request additional information from the payor and reschedule the conference.\n\nWhen it appears that the case meets criteria for a review of the support obligation, you MUST provide the payor with an application for Review &amp; Adjustment or ADMOD (form 470-2749, <i>Request to Modify a Child Support Order</i>) at the conference\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>AEC AGREEMENT IN LIEU OF LISAN</b>\n\nA payor may opt to enter into an AEC Payment Agreement for at least 75% of the IWO rate instead of a LISAN Payment Agreement.\n\nWhen this occurs provide the payor with two forms:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Results of Conference (470-3344)</li>\n \t<li>Payment Agreement (470-3419)</li>\n</ul>\nDO NOT end a LISAN payment agreement which was issued less than one year ago and replace it with an AEC agreement.\n\n<b>UPDATING THE LISAN SCREEN</b>\n\nUpdate the CONF HELD field with a “Y” to generate the Results of Conference. DO NOT update any of the fields related to the payment agreement.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/UpdatingLisanScreenImage.jpg\" />\n\n<b>Generating the AEC Payment Agreement</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Generate the AEC Payment Agreement from FORMOSEL</li>\n \t<li>Use the same payment due date and frequency as in the existing support order</li>\n \t<li>The first payment date should be the first payment due date after the conference is held</li>\n</ul>\nExample:\nConference held: 05/15/14\nObligation due: 1st of each month\nFirst payment: 06/01/14\n\nIf the conference date is very close to the first payment date and there is not sufficient mailing time, set the payment due date according to the order but allow the payor additional time to make the first payment.\n\nExample:\nConference held: 05/29/14\nObligation due: 1st of each month\nFirst payment: 06/01/14\n<ul>\n \t<li>Place a blank copy of the AEC Payment Agreement in PODS. If the payor visits CSRU to sign the agreement and/or make a payment a copy can be printed from PODS.</li>\n</ul>\nWhen a Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued a Notice of Withdrawal will not be issued until the first payment is received. The payor may want to make the payment sooner to avoid a sanction with the licensing agency(s). In this situation, it is a good idea to ask the payor to give you a call when the payment is made to assure the Notice of Withdrawal is issued timely.\n\n<b>Monitoring the AEC Payment Agreement</b>\n\nEven though the agreement is an AEC agreement and <b>NOT</b> a LISAN payment agreement, the LISAN screen remains open until the payor remits the first payment. Once the first payment is received the LISAN screen is ended. This prevents the case from re-selecting for LISAN before the payor is required to make the first payment.\n\nEnter a comment on NARRCASE and the PAYOR screen reflecting there is an AEC agreement, the payment amount and date conference held:\n\nAEC AGMT $300/m 05/20/14\n\nSet a calendar flag (CSRU) or CRM task (EPICS) to monitor for receipt of the first payment.\n\n<b>Payment is NOT received:</b>\nIssue the Certificate of Noncompliance and continue with the LISAN process\n\n<b>Payment IS received:</b>\nEnd the LISAN screen with a reason code of OTH\n\nSet a calendar flag for the worker ID on the CASE screen indicating LISAN ended due to an AEC Agreement\n\nWhen the payor returns the AEC Payment Agreement the office receiving it (CSRU or EPICS) indexes the agreement to PODS catalog.\n\nIf the payor stops remitting payments for at least 75% of the IWO rate, the LISAN selection program will re-select the case when all the criteria are met.\n\nWhen a case re-selects for LISAN because the payor did not remit per the AEC agreement the LISAN process will be followed. The payor will no longer have the option for an AEC agreement in lieu of LISAN.\";i:1582639594373;s:3557:\"<b>Holding the Conference Prior to 10 Days</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>License Sanction Conference, <i>Holding the License Sanction Conference in Less Than Ten Days</i></b>\n\nA payor may request the conference be held before the ten-day waiting period expires. Refer to Title 11-G for instructions.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Issues to be Considered</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, Issues to be Considered in the Conference\n\nThe payor may attempt to discuss case issues other than LISAN (example: balance, payments).\n\nAn ROI (release of information) allows an authorized person to receive the same information as the case party who authorizes the ROI. It does not allow someone to act on behalf of the case party. Therefore, LISAN conferences need to be held with the payor (unless the payor’s attorney is representing him/her for the LISAN or an ROI has Power of Attorney).\n\n<b>Phone Conferences</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> will focus the discussion on issues related to the license sanction. If the payor wants to discuss other case issues staff will first offer the payor a return call from the SRO and make a referral to CSRU. If the payor prefers to call the SRO, EPICS will provide the name and contact number.\n\n<b>In-Person Conference</b>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> will focus the discussion on issues related to the license sanction. If the payor wants to discuss other case issues staff may seek assistance from other staff (if needed) after concluding the license sanction conference.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Payor\'\'s Options</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Results of License Sanction Conference</b>\n\nAt the conference, the payor has the option to do one of the following:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Establish a payment agreement</li>\n \t<li>Pay the support owed</li>\n \t<li>Claim an exemption</li>\n \t<li>Provide an income provider</li>\n \t<li>Request a district court hearing (<b>only</b> if the payor has received from CSRU form 470-3274, <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, or a notice of sanction from the licensing agency within 30 days of notice from licensing agency)</li>\n \t<li>Do nothing, which may result in a license sanction</li>\n</ul>\nDiscuss these options with the payor to determine how to proceed with the license sanction process.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Rescheduling the Conference</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Results of License Sanction Conference</b>.\n\nIt may be necessary to re-schedule a conference:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Payor requests a different date/time</li>\n \t<li>Payor needs additional time to gather financial information</li>\n \t<li>Incomplete financial information is provided</li>\n \t<li>EPICS/CSRU requests additional financial information</li>\n</ul>\nA conference may be re-scheduled one time. However, EPICS/CSRU should allow flexibility and schedule additional conferences as appropriate.\";i:1582639594725;s:15954:\"<b>Establishing a Payment Agreement</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Establishing a Payment Agreement</b>\n\nThe first payment under the License Sanction Payment Agreement is due on the first obligation due date following the conference.\n\nExample of Monthly Obligation:\n<ul>\n \t<li>LISAN Conference is held 04/30/15</li>\n \t<li>Obligation is due the 1st of the month.</li>\n \t<li>Set the payment agreement to start on 05/01/15</li>\n</ul>\nExample of Weekly Obligation:\n<ul>\n \t<li>LISAN Conference is held Friday, 05/15/15</li>\n \t<li>Obligation is due weekly (Thursdays) - next obligation due 05/21/15</li>\n \t<li>Set the payment agreement to start on 05/21/15</li>\n</ul>\nTo avoid issuance of a Certificate of Noncompliance, the first payment <b>AND</b> the signed agreement must be remitted within <span style=\"color: red;\">5</span> days of the start date.\n\nIf a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> has been issued prior to the conference, a <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> will not be issued until the first payment and signed agreement are received.\n\nDuring the LISAN conference EPICS worker will explain the option to make a LISAN payment earlier to withdraw the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> sooner. Include in your narrative that the option was given. EPICS will only lift the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> if the payment is made and the signed agreement is received. After the first payment, the payor must pay according to the start date in the LISAN payment agreement.\n\n(Example: if the start date is 02/15/2018, the payor must submit his/her payment by the 15th of each month.)\n\n<b>PHONE CONFERENCES and Payment Agreements</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> places an unsigned copy of the <i>License Sanction Payment Agreement</i> (470-3344) in PODS. In the event a payor visits CSRU to make the initial payment and/or sign the agreement, a copy may be printed from PODS.\n\n<b>CSRU will:</b>\n<ol>\n \t<li>Follow normal office protocol for verifying and receipting the payment, if one is brought in.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU worker signs the payment agreement and gives a copy to the customer at the counter.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU sends EPICS an urgent referral, noting signed payment agreement and lisan payment have been received.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU scans and catalogs the signed payment agreement into PODS</li>\n</ol>\n<b>EPICS will:</b>\n<ol>\n \t<li>EPICS worker receives the urgent referral from CSRU.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker reviews the case to issue a Withdrawal of Non-Compliance if needed.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker updates the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen with the date the payment agreement was signed by the CSRU worker.</li>\n</ol>\n<b>IN PERSON CONFERENCE</b>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> may have instances when the payor signs the payment agreement and makes the initial payment at the time of the conference. Follow normal office protocol for verifying and receipting the payment.\n\n<b>CSRU</b> updates the LISAN screen and places a signed copy of the payment agreement in PODS catalog.\n\nEPICS will monitor the payment agreement upon receipt of appropriate calendar flags.\n\nDO NOT end a LISAN payment agreement which was issued less than one year ago and replace it with an AEC agreement. See <b>AEC AGREEMENT IN LIEU OF LISAN</b> below.\n\nIf a Certificate of Noncompliance was previously issued it is necessary to send an Urgent referral to EPICS when the payor makes a payment at CSRU. For more information on LISAN payments received at CSRU see <b>Payments Received at CSRU Checking CASESTAT</b> below.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>AEC AGREEMENT IN LIEU OF LISAN</b>\n\nA payor may opt to enter into an AEC Payment Agreement for at least 75% of the IWO rate instead of a LISAN Payment Agreement.\n\nWhen this occurs provide the payor with two forms:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Results of Conference (470-3344)</li>\n \t<li>Payment Agreement (470-3419)</li>\n</ul>\nDO NOT end a LISAN payment agreement which was issued less than one year ago and replace it with an AEC agreement.\n\n<b>UPDATING THE LISAN SCREEN</b>\n\nUpdate the CONF HELD field with a “Y” to generate the Results of Conference. DO NOT update any of the fields related to the payment agreement.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/UpdatingLisanScreenImage.jpg\" />\n\n<b>Generating the AEC Payment Agreement</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Generate the AEC Payment Agreement from FORMOSEL</li>\n \t<li>Use the same payment due date and frequency as in the existing support order</li>\n \t<li>The first payment date should be the first payment due date after the conference is held</li>\n</ul>\nExample:\nConference held: 05/15/14\nObligation due: 1st of each month\nFirst payment: 06/01/14\n\nIf the conference date is very close to the first payment date and there is not sufficient mailing time, set the payment due date according to the order but allow the payor additional time to make the first payment.\n\nExample:\nConference held: 05/29/14\nObligation due: 1st of each month\nFirst payment: 06/01/14\n<ul>\n \t<li>Place a blank copy of the AEC Payment Agreement in PODS. If the payor visits CSRU to sign the agreement and/or make a payment a copy can be printed from PODS.</li>\n</ul>\nWhen a Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued a Notice of Withdrawal will not be issued until the first payment is received. The payor may want to make the payment sooner to avoid a sanction with the licensing agency(s). In this situation, it is a good idea to ask the payor to give you a call when the payment is made to assure the Notice of Withdrawal is issued timely.\n\n<b>Monitoring the AEC Payment Agreement</b>\n\nEven though the agreement is an AEC agreement and <b>NOT</b> a LISAN payment agreement, the LISAN screen remains open until the payor remits the first payment. Once the first payment is received the LISAN screen is ended. This prevents the case from re-selecting for LISAN before the payor is required to make the first payment.\n\nEnter a comment on NARRCASE and the PAYOR screen reflecting there is an AEC agreement, the payment amount and date conference held:\n\nAEC AGMT $300/m 05/20/14\n\nSet a calendar flag (CSRU) or CRM task (EPICS) to monitor for receipt of the first payment.\n\n<b>Payment is NOT received:</b>\nIssue the Certificate of Noncompliance and continue with the LISAN process\n\n<b>Payment IS received:</b>\nEnd the LISAN screen with a reason code of OTH\n\nSet a calendar flag for the worker ID on the CASE screen indicating LISAN ended due to an AEC Agreement\n\nWhen the payor returns the AEC Payment Agreement the office receiving it (CSRU or EPICS) indexes the agreement to PODS catalog.\n\nIf the payor stops remitting payments for at least 75% of the IWO rate, the LISAN selection program will re-select the case when all the criteria are met.\n\nWhen a case re-selects for LISAN because the payor did not remit per the AEC agreement the LISAN process will be followed. The payor will no longer have the option for an AEC agreement in lieu of LISAN.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Payments Received at CSRU - Checking CASESTAT</b>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> staff accepting payments at the customer window review CASESTAT for an open LISAN or CONTEMPT screen. The appropriate/assigned worker (if different than the person receiving the payment) is notified. That worker reviews narratives and the LISAN screen and makes a referral to EPICS if a Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued, or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\n\nIf the Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued in the last 30-35 days send an URGENT referral to EPICS. Urgent referrals are worked the same day. This may avoid a sanction with the licensing agency(s).\n\nCSRU may wish to post a notice at the customer window asking customers to tell staff if a payment is for a license sanction, contempt or administrative levy action. See <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/Payment%20Poster.doc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> Payment Poster example</b></a>.\n<p style=\"color: red;\">If the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen is blank, CSRU staff should ask the payor if the payment agreement has been signed and returned. If the payor has not yet mailed the agreement, a copy can be printed from PODS for the payor to sign.</p>\n<b style=\"color: red;\">CSRU will:</b>\n<ol style=\"color: red;\">\n \t<li>Follow normal office protocol for verifying and receipting the payment.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU worker signs the payment agreement and gives a copy to the customer at the counter.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU sends EPICS an <b>urgent referral</b>, noting signed payment agreement and LISAN payment have been received.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU scans and <b>catalogs</b> the signed payment agreement.</li>\n</ol>\n<b style=\"color: red;\">EPICS will:</b>\n<ol style=\"color: red;\">\n \t<li>EPICS worker Receives the urgent referral from CSRU.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker Reviews the case to issues a <i>Withdrawal of Non-Compliance</i> if needed.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker Updates the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen with the date the payment agreement was signed by the CSRU worker.</li>\n</ol>\nCASE REVIEWS:\n\nWhen completing a Case Review, check CASESTAT for open LISAN and Contempt screens. Also review narratives and PAYHIST. Send a referral to EPICS if a noncompliance has been issued and payments are being received or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Calculating Payments</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, Results of License Sanction Conference, <i>Monitoring the Payment Agreement</i>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> receives the calendar flags which issue from the payment agreement monitoring program.\n\nThe payment agreement monitoring program runs the second Friday of each month. The program reviews only the previous month\'\'s payments to determine whether the payor is in compliance with the payment agreement.\n\nEPICS reviews for payments received between issuance of the flag and review of the case. The <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> is issued when appropriate.\n\n<b>Calculating the \'\'Lifetime\'\' of the Payment Agreement</b>\n\nWhen a license sanction (LISAN) payment agreement is entered on a case, ICAR begins monitoring cases for incoming payments. One of the payment monitoring calculations is referred to as a \'\'lifetime\'\' payment agreement calculation.\n\nICAR calculates how <b>much is due</b> under the \'\'lifetime\'\' of the LISAN payment agreement by:\n<ol>\n \t<li>Counting the number of months due from the date in the START field through the end of the most recent month (ICAR converts the frequency to monthly if any other frequency is entered.), and</li>\n \t<li>Multiplying the payment agreement amount by the number of months the payment agreement has been due, and</li>\n \t<li>ICAR reviews the REG payments received during that same lifetime of the payment agreement. ICAR then compares the amount due to the amount paid for the lifetime of the payment agreement.</li>\n \t<li>If the amount paid is greater than the amount due and there\'\'s a sanction in place ICAR, issues calendar flag: LISAN 28 and narrative Lisan 54 to the EPICS worker for that case.</li>\n</ol>\nThe EPICS worker reviews the case and issues a <i>Notice Of Withdrawal Of Certificate Of Noncompliance</i> 470-3275 if appropriate, and adds a narrative to the case which includes the \'\'lifetime\'\' payment agreement calculation. (Examples of ICAR\'\'s calculation are below.)\n\nThe \'\'lifetime\'\' LISAN payment agreement monitoring/calculation program does not include MIW, IWO, or UIB payments received. If a MIW, IWO, or UIB payment is received in a month, <b>that month will be excluded</b> from the \'\'lifetime\'\' calculations for payments due and for payments received. (This is <b>only</b> for the calculations of the lifetime payment agreement.)\n\n<b>Example 1:</b> A case has a LISAN payment agreement for $10/month starting 05/01/2013 and ending 09/30/2013.\n\n[ninja_tables id=\"932\"]\n\nThe $50 MIW payment (received in 07/2013) will not be added to the LISAN payments \"received\" calculation and will not be added to the payment \"due\" calculation for the same month (07/2013). ICAR will calculate the totals for the lifetime of the payment agreement above as: Payments Due = $40, Payments Received = $20.\n\n<b>Example 2:</b> A case has a LISAN payment agreement for $10/month starting 05/01/2013 and ending 09/30/2013.\n\n[ninja_tables id=\"933\"]\n\nThe totals calculated for the lifetime of the payment agreement above will be: Payments Due = $40, Payments Received = $20.\n\nThis payor made a REG payment in the same month as the MIW payment. Since, that month is excluded from payments due; all payments received in that month are excluded (the REG payment is also excluded).\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Length of the Payment Agreement</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Results of License Sanction Conference, <i>Length of the Payment Agreement</i> When a signed payment agreement exceeds one year:</b>\n\nICAR issues calendar flag LISAN19.\n\nLISAN payment agreement signed one year ago. Review to determine status of the LISAN process.\n\n<b>EPICS</b> receives calendar flag LISAN19. The LISAN process screen is ended with a reason code of OTH. A status letter is sent to the payor to explain the payment agreement has expired and payments need to resume for the amount set in the court order. The case will re-select for LISAN when all criteria are met again.\n\nEXCEPTIONS:\n<ul>\n \t<li>There is a current exemption (exemption not expired)</li>\n \t<li>There is a Certificate of Noncompliance in place</li>\n \t<li>The case is in a Review or Modification action; see <a href=\"http://www.readbag.com/dhs-state-ia-us-policyanalysis-policymanualpages-manual-documents-rules-441-98\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>IAC 441-98.104(3)</b></a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Sending a Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance when there is a Payment Agreement</b>\n\n<b>If the payor signs the payment agreement and then reports an employer, would the payor be required to make up any missed payments before the Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance could be issued?</b>\n<ol>\n \t<li>When an IWO is initiated and you verify the payor is employed and MIW payments will be received, you are required to issue a <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>.</li>\n \t<li>If the payor has signed a payment agreement, misses payments, and an IWO is initiated, determine if MIW payments were received on <b>any</b> of the payor’s cases after the IWO was initiated.\n<ul>\n \t<li>If MIW payments began, the MIW payments caused a break in the payment agreement. The payor is required to make up any missed payments prior to the beginning of the MIW payments. ICAR monitors for the lifetime of the payment agreement and each month needs a REG payment if there is not an MIW/UIB payment.</li>\n \t<li>If MIW payments did not begin, the payor is required to make up all missed payments since the start of the payment agreement.</li>\n \t<li>If the MIW payments end, the payor is required to begin paying on the payment agreement. The payor would be required to begin making payments in accordance with the previously signed payment agreement.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\";i:1582639595053;s:3823:\"<b>Issuing results of license sanction conference</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Results of License Sanction Conference</b>\n\n<b>ALWAYS</b> issue form 470-3344, <i>Results of License Sanction Conference</i>, to inform the payor of the results of the conference. Place a copy of the form in PODS catalog.\n\nWhen a copy of the payment agreement is mailed to the payor include additional comments on the form stating the <b>date</b> the signed agreement and <span style=\"color: red;\">first</span> payment are due (<span style=\"color: red;\">next obligation due date after the conference</span>).\n\nIf you determine that the case may be eligible for a review or administrative modification of the support obligation, you <b>MUST</b> provide the payor with an application (form 470-2749, <i>Request to Modify A Child Support Order</i>). The license sanction continues while the review is being completed. However, if the review results in a modification of the order, end the license sanction to allow the payor an opportunity to pay the support due under the new obligation.\n\nBe sure to explain to the payor that the final determination of whether the case is eligible for a review of the support obligation will be determined by the R&amp;A worker.\n\n<b>ALWAYS</b> enter a summary narrative detailing the conference.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Payor claims an exemption</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Results of License Sanction Conference, <i>Exempting the Payor from the License Sanction Process</i>.</b>\n\nDuring the conference, you may determine that the payor qualifies for an exemption from the license sanction process.\n\n<b> Total/Permanent Disability</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> sets the exemption period for one year and sends a referral to CSRU when the payor returns a physician\'\'s statement indicating a total/permanent disability. <span style=\"color: red;\">When the exemption period expires make a CSRU referral.</span>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> reviews the case to see if case closure criteria is met <span style=\"color: red;\">and for the next appropriate action.</span>\n\n<b>Welfare to Work (WTW)</b>\n\nWTW is not considered an exemption from the license sanction process if the payor enrolls in the program <b>AFTER</b> the process is initiated. The case selection program will bypass the payor from the license sanction process when initially reviewing the case for license sanction criteria.\n\n<b>Parental Obligation Pilot Project (POPP)/ REACH Grant</b>\n\nParticipation in POPP/REACH is considered an exemption from the license sanction process. The case selection program will bypass the payor from the license sanction process when initially reviewing the case for license sanction criteria. Central office staff reviews a list of POPP participants and sends a referral to EPICS when the process has already been initiated. EPICS takes appropriate steps to end the LISAN process.\n\n<b>Food Stamps &amp; Job-seekling/Job-training</b>\n\nIf the payor is receiving food stamps and participating in a job-seeking or job-training program through Iowa Workforce Development, see the Income Maintenance manual <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/7-m.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 7-M, Food Stamp Employment and Training Program</b></a> (broken link) to determine availability of this program and the subsequent exemption.\";i:1582639595368;s:11382:\"Form 470-3274, <i>Certificate Of Noncompliance</i>, directs the licensing agency to initiate steps to suspend, revoke, deny issuance or deny renewal of the obligor’s licenses and/or motor vehicle registrations.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Issuing a Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> reviews cases and issues the Certificate of Noncompliance upon receipt of calendar flags. This includes cases with the obligation suspended due to a change of custody. See Bypassing Case Selection below. A copy of the Certificate of Noncompliance is placed in PODS catalog.\n\n<b>EPICS</b> reviews the balance before issuing the Certificate of Noncompliance. A payor\'\'s support payments MUST be delinquent in an amount equal to the support payment for three months.\n\nEXCEPTION: A signed payment agreement exists.\n\nEPICS will review a case with no verified address for level one location. If a new address is not found EPICS will send the Certificate of Noncompliance to the last known address.\n\n<b>CSRU</b> receives calendar flag LISAN14 90 days after the Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued and LISAN 20 after one year. Review the case for further enforcement per office protocol.\n\n<b>LISAN 14:</b>\n\nLISAN Certificate of Noncompliance sent to licensing agency or agencies 90 days ago. Review the case for further enforcement.\n\n<b>LISAN 20:</b>\n\nLISAN Certificate of Noncompliance sent to licensing agency or agencies 1 year ago. Review the case for further enforcement.\n\nWhen CSRU receives notice of any bankruptcy action, update the BANKRUPTCY &amp; CHAPTR fields on the PAYOR screen. Review CASESTAT. If LISAN is active make a referral to EPICS.\n\nDue to the short duration of the Chapter 7 bankruptcy and because of the possibility of sanctions against CSRU, it is recommended to wait until the plan is dismissed or discharged before continuing license sanction proceedings.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Sending a Certificate of Noncompliance to Licensing Agencies</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> accesses the LSAGENCY screen on ICAR for the name of the licensing agency\'\'s contact. Access LISAN BPH - Desk Aids/LISAN Contacts below for the fax number of each agency.\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>Department of Transportation (DOT)</b>\nICAR interfaces electronically with DOT\'\'s licensing database. When you enter a date in the gen cert of noncom field on the LISAN screen for a case, ICAR creates and sends a sanction record to DOT. DO NOT mail or fax the form.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Natural Resources (DNR)</b>\nFAX the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the attention of the contact individual.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Public Health (DPH)</b>\nE-mail the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the email on the form and enter in the subject line: CSRU, {payor last name, payor first name}, {ICAR case #} Example: CSRU: Smith, John, #11111</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Commerce - Iowa Insurance Division</b>\nEmail the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the email on the form and enter in the Subject line: CSRU Certificate of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Commerce - Division of Banking/Iowa Professional Licensing Division</b>\nEmail the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the email on the form and enter in the subject line: CSRU Certificate of Noncompliance or CSRU Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Inspections and Appeals (DIA)</b>\nFAX the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the attention of the contact individual.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Public Safety (DPS)</b>\nFAX the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the attention of the contact individual.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction Returned After You Send the Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> may receive the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i> from the USPS as undeliverable after the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> has already been sent to the licensing agency.\n\nWhen this occurs enter:\n<ul>\n \t<li>The current date in the GEN WITHDRAWAL OF NONCOM field.</li>\n \t<li>The reason code \"RTN\" in the GEN WITHDRAWAL OF NONCOM WHY field.</li>\n \t<li>The current date in the PROCESS ENDED field.</li>\n \t<li>The reason code \"LOC\" in the PROCESS ENDED WHY field.</li>\n</ul>\nBecause the payor did not receive the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i> informing him/her of the pending action, you must withdraw the license sanction and reinitiate the license sanction process by allowing ICAR to again select the case for license sanction.\n\nSee EPICS <b>RETURN MAIL PROCESSING</b> below.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Case Selection</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Case Selection, <i>ICAR Case Selection Criteria</i></b>.\n\n<b>ICAR Case Selection</b>\n\nICAR selects cases for license sanction based on certain criteria. The license sanction case selection program runs the weekend after the last working day of the month.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Bypassing Case Selection</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Screens Used in License Sanction Process, <i>CASESTAT Screen</i></b>\n\nThe LISAN process should be bypassed in the following situations:\n<ul>\n \t<li>CSRU holds an Administrative Enforcement Conference (AEC) <b>and</b> the payor enters into an AEC payment agreement</li>\n \t<li>Current support obligation suspended due to change of custody AND\n<ul>\n \t<li>Obligation is suspended for all children covered by the order</li>\n \t<li>Child(ren) is a minor</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li>Payee is deceased and child(ren) are residing with the payor</li>\n \t<li>SRO/SRS determine LISAN is not an appropriate enforcement action</li>\n \t<li style=\"color: red;\">Case has been referred to the attorney for a contempt action</li>\n</ul>\n<b>When LISAN had NOT already selected:</b>\n\n<i>CSRU</i> enters the bypass on the CASESTAT screen.\n\n<b>When LISAN is currently active:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>CSRU</i>Review the case and narrate whether LISAN continues to be an appropriate enforcement action.\n\nProcess end LISAN and enter the bypass on the CASESTAT screen when a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance (Form 470-3274)</i> is <b>NOT</b> in effect.\n\nWhen a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> <b>IS</b> in effect and LISAN is no longer appropriate, send an EPICS referral. Enter a bypass on the CASESTAT screen <b>after</b> EPICS has issued the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance (Form 470-3275)</i> and has process ended the LISAN screen.</li>\n \t<li><i>EPICS</i>Issue the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance (Form 470-3275)</i> upon receiving a CSRU referral.\n\nProcess end the LISAN screen (CSRU enters bypass; see above)\n\nCalendar Flags LISAN 47 and 48 will issue to the worker ID entering the bypass. The worker entering the bypass is responsible for updating or canceling the bypass</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>LISAN Contacts</b>\n\n<b>Department of Transportation</b>\nPO Box 9204\nDes Moines, IA 50306-9204\n<i>Forms are sent electronically</i>\n\n<b>Department of Natural Resources</b>\nLaw Enforcement Bureau 4th Floor\nWallace State Office Building\n502 East 9th Street\nDes Moines, Iowa 50319-0034\n<i>Forms are sent electronically</i>\n\n<b>Department of Public Health</b>\nLucas State Office Building\nBureau of Professional Licensure\nDes Moines, IA 50319-0075\n515-281-0233 (phone)\n\nForms are sent via email to: Attention: Beth Jorgenson*\n*Beth is the contact for the Bureau of Professional Licensure only. See the LSAGENCY screen on ICAR for the contact name for the specific license type.\n\n<b>Department of Commerce</b>\n\n<b>Professional Licensing and Regulation Division</b>\n200 East Grand Ave., Set. 350\nDes Moines, IA 50309\n515-725-9030 (phone)\n\nForms are sent via email to:\nAttention: Lori SchraderBachar\n\n<b>Iowa Insurance Division</b>\nTwo Ruan Center\n601 Locust - 4th Floor\nDes Moines, IA 50309-3738\n515-281-4735 (phone)\n\nForms are sent via email to:\nAttention: Hilary Foster\n\n<b>Department of Inspections and Appeals</b>\n\nIowa Racing and Gaming Commission\n717 East Court, Suite B\nDes Moines, IA 50309\n515-281-7355 (phone)\n515-242-6560 (fax)\n\nForms are sent via <span style=\"color: red;\">email</span> to:\n<a href=\"mailto:barb.blake@iowa.gov\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">barb.blake@iowa.gov</a>\n\n<b>Department of Public Safety</b>\n\nProgram Services Bureau\n215 East 7th St.\nDes Moines, IA 50319-0045\n515-725-6231 (phone)\n515-725-6264 (fax)\n\nForms are sent via fax to:\nAttention: Lisa Lampe\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Return Mail Processing (EPICS)</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> mails all LISAN forms to payors/payees in envelopes with EPICS return address and processes return mail as follows:\n\n<b>USPS Provides a New Address:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>Update ICAR with the new address information</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</li>\n \t<li>Update LISAN screen</li>\n \t<li>Regenerate notice prior to re-mailing</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Issue Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li>Wait 1 day and then update payor\'\'s address and re-issue the Certificate of Noncompliance</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>All other forms</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Re-mail to payor/payee</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<b>USPS Does Not Provide a New Address</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Remove invalid address from ICAR</li>\n \t<li>Complete location searches on the following on-line resources:\n<ul>\n \t<li>ICON</li>\n \t<li>IABC/ELIAS</li>\n \t<li>VRT</li>\n \t<li>LOCDB</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li>Review any unverified/hidden addresses on ADDVER (ADDVERSUM). Update if appropriate.</li>\n \t<li><b>Address is Located</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Update LISAN screen</li>\n \t<li>Regenerate notice prior to re-mailing</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Issue Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li>Wait 1 day and then update payor\'\'s address and re-issue the Certificate of Noncompliance</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>All other forms</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Re-mail to payor/payee</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><b>No Address is Located</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Update LISAN screen</li>\n \t<li>Make a referral to the office assigned to the case for additional location</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Do NOT issue a Withdrawal of Noncompliance as only required to send to the last known address</li>\n \t<li>Make a referral to the office assigned to the case for additional location</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n \t<li><i>All other forms</i>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Make a referral to the office assigned to the case for additional location</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\";i:1582639595685;s:5425:\"<b>BEFORE Referring a Case to Another State for Enforcement</b>\n\nDetermine if there is an active license sanction action on the case. If so, before sending the referral to the other state, ensure that the payor:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Does not have a valid exemption from license sanction,</li>\n \t<li>Does not have a conference scheduled for a future date,</li>\n \t<li>Does not have a district court hearing scheduled for a future date,</li>\n \t<li>Is not paying on a license sanction payment agreement,</li>\n \t<li>Has had a license sanction in place for at least 90 days and,</li>\n \t<li>Is not responding to Iowa\'\'s license sanction action, and you attempted to contact the payor by telephone to discuss the license sanction.</li>\n</ul>\nWhen these criteria are met, you may review the case to determine if you want to refer the case to another state for further enforcement actions.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>REFERRING the Case to Another State for Enforcement</b>\n\nIf the responding state will not pursue enforcement actions when Iowa has an active license sanction action, make a referral to EPICS to process-end the LISAN screen.\n<ul>\n \t<li>When sending the referral packet to the responding state, clearly narrate in the Additional Case Information section on the Transmittal 1 that Iowa has an active license sanction process against Iowa licenses.</li>\n \t<li>Link the INTERSTA and LISAN screens. ICAR then generates to your local printer the appropriate statuses regarding Iowa\'\'s license sanction actions. Send the statuses to the responding state.</li>\n \t<li>Communicate all license sanction actions with the responding state. Generate a status from the INTERST2 screen with additional information when you believe the responding state needs further information.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Communication is key when continuing a license sanction on a case while pursuing an Iowa-initiated interstate referral.</b>\n\n<b>Contact With the Payor After Sending the Interstate Referral</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>If the payor contacts Iowa about releasing the sanction:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Tell the payor to contact the responding state, or</li>\n \t<li>Obtain the payor\'\'s phone number and have the responding state call the payor.</li>\n \t<li><i>Follow-up with the responding state</i> to determine if the state wants you to release the license sanction.</li>\n \t<li>Create a manual calendar flag reminding you to follow-up with the responding state.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\nIf you have any questions regarding working with another state, see your supervisor.\n<ul>\n \t<li>If the payor shows up at your office and wants to make a payment, accept the payment and refer to <b>Payments Received at CSRU</b> below. Also call the responding state so they are aware of the payment. For some cases, you may want to proceed with a license sanction payment agreement. Discuss the case with your supervisor to determine how to proceed.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Payments Received at CSRU - Checking CASESTAT</b>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> staff accepting payments at the customer window review CASESTAT for an open LISAN or CONTEMPT screen. The appropriate/assigned worker (if different than the person receiving the payment) is notified. That worker reviews narratives and the LISAN screen and makes a referral to EPICS if a Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued, or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\n\nIf the Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued in the last 30-35 days send an URGENT referral to EPICS. Urgent referrals are worked the same day. This may avoid a sanction with the licensing agency(s).\n\nCSRU may wish to post a notice at the customer window asking customers to tell staff if a payment is for a license sanction, contempt or administrative levy action. See <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/Payment%20Poster.doc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> Payment Poster example</b></a>.\n<p style=\"color: red;\">If the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen is blank, CSRU staff should ask the payor if the payment agreement has been signed and returned. If the payor has not yet mailed the agreement, a copy can be printed from PODS for the payor to sign.</p>\n<b style=\"color: red;\">CSRU will:</b>\n<ol style=\"color: red;\">\n \t<li>Follow normal office protocol for verifying and receipting the payment.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU worker signs the payment agreement and gives a copy to the customer at the counter.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU sends EPICS an <b>urgent referral</b>, noting signed payment agreement and LISAN payment have been received.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU scans and <b>catalogs</b> the signed payment agreement.</li>\n</ol>\n<b style=\"color: red;\">EPICS will:</b>\n<ol style=\"color: red;\">\n \t<li>EPICS worker Receives the urgent referral from CSRU.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker Reviews the case to issues a <i>Withdrawal of Non-Compliance</i> if needed.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker Updates the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen with the date the payment agreement was signed by the CSRU worker.</li>\n</ol>\nCASE REVIEWS:\n\nWhen completing a Case Review, check CASESTAT for open LISAN and Contempt screens. Also review narratives and PAYHIST. Send a referral to EPICS if a noncompliance has been issued and payments are being received or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\";i:1582639596021;s:6629:\"Form 470-3275, <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, directs the licensing agency to terminate all license sanction proceeding against the payor.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Issuing a Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\nSee <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\nEPICS reviews cases and issues the Notice of Withdrawal of certificate of Noncompliance upon receipt of calendar flags and referrals from CSRU. Place a copy of the form in PODS.\n\nParticipating in Welfare to Work (WTW) does not require that a <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> be issued if the payor enrolles in the program AFTER the license sanction is initiated.\n\nParticipating in the Parental Obligation Pilot Project (POPP) or REACH grant DOES require that a Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance be issued if the payor enrolls in the program AFTER the license sanction is initiated\n\nWhen CSRU receives notice of any bankruptcy action, update the BANKRUPTCY &amp; CHAPTR fields on the PAYOR screen. Review CASESTAT. If LISAN is active make a referral to EPICS.\n\nDue to the short duration of the Chapter 7 bankruptcy and because of the possibility of sanctions against CSRU, it is recommended to wait until the plan is dismissed or discharged before continuing license sanction proceedings.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Sending a Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance\nto Licensing Agencies</b>\n\nEPICS accesses the LSAGENCY screen on ICAR for the name of the licensing agency\'\'s contact. Access <b>LISAN BPH - Desk Aids/LISAN Contacts</b> below for the fax number of each agency.\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>Department of Transportation (DOT)</b>ICAR interfaces electronically with DOT\'\'s licensing database. When you enter a date in the gen withdrawal of noncom field on the LISAN screen for a case, ICAR creates and sends a withdrawal record to DOT. DO NOT mail or fax the form.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Natural Resources (DNR)</b>FAX the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the attention of the contact individual.\n\nWhen faxing the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the DNR, complete the following steps:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Fax the form to DNR at the following number:\n515-281-7147\nAttn: Marla Gallardo</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<b>EPICS</b> staff set a task on the CRM for the DNR specialists to enter a withdrawal on DNR’s automated system.\n\nOnce the specialist processes the task they will narrate one of the following:\n<ul>\n \t<li>The request to withdraw the DNR license sanction has been processed.</li>\n \t<li>The request to withdraw the DNR license sanction has been processed. If the payor has additional questions regarding a DNR license sanction, the payor should contact DNR.</li>\n \t<li>The request to withdraw the DNR license sanction cannot be processed. The payor has another ICAR case with a CSRU DNR license sanction in process.</li>\n</ul>\nWhen issuing a <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to DNR, <b>please remember to check for multiple cases for the payor</b>. There may be another case for the payor that should <b>not</b> have the license sanction action withdrawn at DNR.\n\nDNR enters a sanction on their ELSI system only once for a payor, even when the payor has multiple cases. <b>Therefore, unless you wish to withdraw the license sanction action on all of the payor\'\'s cases, do not refer the case to the DNR specialist.</b>\n\nYou should, though, continue to fax the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to DNR for the case for which you are issuing the withdrawal.\n\n<hr />\n\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>Department of Public Health (DPH)</b>\nE-mail the Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance to the email on the form and enter in the subject line: CSRU, {payor last name, payor first name}, {ICAR case #} Example: CSRU: Smith, John, #11111</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Commerce - Iowa Insurance Division</b>\nEmail the Certificate of Noncompliance to the email on the form and enter in the subject line: CSRU Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Commerce - Division of Banking/Iowa Professional Licensing Division</b>\nEmail the Certificate of Noncompliance to the email on the form and enter in the subject line: CSRU Certificate of Noncompliance or CSRU Withdrawal of Noncompliance</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Inspections and Appeals (DIA)</b>\nFAX the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the attention of the contact individual.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Public Safety (DPS)</b>\nFAX the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to the attention of the contact individual.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>LISAN Contacts</b>\n\n<b>Department of Transportation</b>\nPO Box 9204\nDes Moines, IA 50306-9204\n<i>Forms are sent electronically</i>\n\n<b>Department of Natural Resources</b>\nLaw Enforcement Bureau 4th Floor\nWallace State Office Building\n502 East 9th Street\nDes Moines, Iowa 50319-0034\n<i>Forms are sent electronically</i>\n\n<b>Department of Public Health</b>\nLucas State Office Building\nBureau of Professional Licensure\nDes Moines, IA 50319-0075\n515-281-0233 (phone)\n\nForms are sent via email to: Attention: Beth Jorgenson*\n*Beth is the contact for the Bureau of Professional Licensure only. See the LSAGENCY screen on ICAR for the contact name for the specific license type.\n\n<b>Department of Commerce</b>\n\n<b>Professional Licensing and Regulation Division</b>\n200 East Grand Ave., Set. 350\nDes Moines, IA 50309\n515-725-9030 (phone)\n\nForms are sent via email to:\nAttention: Lori SchraderBachar\n\n<b>Iowa Insurance Division</b>\nTwo Ruan Center\n601 Locust - 4th Floor\nDes Moines, IA 50309-3738\n515-281-4735 (phone)\n\nForms are sent via email to:\nAttention: Hilary Foster\n\n<b>Department of Inspections and Appeals</b>\n\nIowa Racing and Gaming Commission\n717 East Court, Suite B\nDes Moines, IA 50309\n515-281-7355 (phone)\n515-242-6560 (fax)\n\nForms are sent via <span style=\"color: red;\">email</span> to:\n<a href=\"mailto:barb.blake@iowa.gov\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">barb.blake@iowa.gov</a>\n\n<b>Department of Public Safety</b>\n\nProgram Services Bureau\n215 East 7th St.\nDes Moines, IA 50319-0045\n515-725-6231 (phone)\n515-725-6264 (fax)\n\nForms are sent via fax to:\nAttention: Lisa Lampe\";i:1582639596310;s:2067:\"See <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>District Court Hearing</b>\n\n<b>REQUEST IS RECEIVED FROM THE CLERK OF COURT</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Send an e-mail to the CSRU Policy - LISAN distribution list advising of the hearing request/Order for Hearing (include the CSRU Office Mailbox and CSRU SRS with a \"cc\"). Policy staff will contact the licensing agency(s) to confirm they have received the Notice of Hearing from the COC and stayed the action.</li>\n \t<li>Send request/order for hearing to CSRU through PODS by indexing the request to the worker ID shown on the CASE screen. Forward the original document(s) to CSRU via local mail.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS should take no further action on the LISAN pending outcome of the hearing.</li>\n</ul>\nWhen a payment agreement is mailed to the payor for review and a hearing request is submitted BEFORE the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> is issued, EPICS <span style=\"color: red;\">will</span> issue the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> <span style=\"color: red;\">immediately</span>.\n\n<b>CSRU</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>When request/order is received at CSRU send an e-mail to the CSRU Policy - LISAN distribution list and send an URGENT referral to EPICS. Policy staff will contact the licensing agency(s) to confirm they have received the Notice of Hearing from the COC and stayed the action.</li>\n \t<li>Complete the LISAN2 screen and follow all steps listed in the manual under Responsibilities of the Unit and Results of District Court Hearing.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>REQUEST IS RECEIVED FROM THE PAYOR</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Send an email to the CSRU mailbox with a \"cc\" to the office supervisor informing them of the payor\'\'s request for hearing.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>CSRU</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Contact the payor and notify him/her that the request MUST be filed with the court in the county where the child support order is filed.</li>\n</ul>\";i:1582639596645;s:1810:\"See <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> Title 11-G</b></a>, <b>Ending the License Sanction Process</b>\n\n<b>EPICS</b> receives calendar flags and referrals from CSRU about ending the LISAN process. EPICS reviews the cases and process ends the license sanction process when appropriate.\n\n<b>Modification Order is Filed - or - New Obligation is Added - or - A New Obligation Amount Begins</b>\n\n<b>CSRU</b> sends a referral to EPICS when:\n<ul>\n \t<li>LISAN process is active - <b>AND</b> - A signed LISAN payment agreement exists</li>\n \t<li>LISAN process is active - <b>AND</b> - <span style=\"color: red;\">A Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued</span></li>\n</ul>\n<b>EPICS</b> reviews and takes appropriate steps in the LISAN process.\n\nWhen a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> is in place, the payor needs to make up the total amount owed on the lifetime of the LISAN payment agreement. Once this is paid EPICS will review to lift the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> and process end the LISAN screen. This is when the obligation has been modified up or down.\n\nEND the LISAN process only when:\n<ul>\n \t<li>A modification order is filed or a new obligation amount is added/begins - <b>AND</b></li>\n \t<li>There is a signed payment agreement in place - <b>AND</b> -</li>\n \t<li>A Certificate of Noncompliance has NOT been issued\n- <b>OR</b> -</li>\n \t<li>A <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> HAS been issued - <b>AND</b> -</li>\n \t<li>All payments have been made per the existing payment agreement - <b>AND</b> -</li>\n \t<li style=\"color: red;\">A <i>Notice of Withdrawal Of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> has been issued</li>\n</ul>\";i:1582639596917;s:634:\"All staff who accepts payments at the customer window will review CASESTAT for open LISAN or Contempt screen. Appropriate/assigned worker (if different than person receiving payment) is notified. That worker is expected to review narratives and refer to EPICS/LISAN if a noncompliance has been issued, or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\n\nWhen completing a Case Review, CASESTAT is to be checked for open LISAN and Contempt screens and narratives will be reviewed to determine if referral to EPICS/LISAN needed as noncompliance has been issued, or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\";i:1582639597254;s:2433:\"<b>CSRU</b> staff accepting payments at the customer window review CASESTAT for an open LISAN or CONTEMPT screen. The appropriate/assigned worker (if different than the person receiving the payment) is notified. That worker reviews narratives and the LISAN screen and makes a referral to EPICS if a Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued, or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\n\nIf the Certificate of Noncompliance has been issued in the last 30-35 days send an URGENT referral to EPICS. Urgent referrals are worked the same day. This may avoid a sanction with the licensing agency(s).\n\nCSRU may wish to post a notice at the customer window asking customers to tell staff if a payment is for a license sanction, contempt or administrative levy action. See <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/LISAN/Contents/DeskAids/Payment%20Poster.doc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> Payment Poster example</b></a>.\n<p style=\"color: red;\">If the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen is blank, CSRU staff should ask the payor if the payment agreement has been signed and returned. If the payor has not yet mailed the agreement, a copy can be printed from PODS for the payor to sign.</p>\n<b style=\"color: red;\">CSRU will:</b>\n<ol style=\"color: red;\">\n \t<li>Follow normal office protocol for verifying and receipting the payment.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU worker signs the payment agreement and gives a copy to the customer at the counter.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU sends EPICS an <b>urgent referral</b>, noting signed payment agreement and LISAN payment have been received.</li>\n \t<li>CSRU scans and <b>catalogs</b> the signed payment agreement.</li>\n</ol>\n<b style=\"color: red;\">EPICS will:</b>\n<ol style=\"color: red;\">\n \t<li>EPICS worker Receives the urgent referral from CSRU.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker Reviews the case to issues a <i>Withdrawal of Non-Compliance</i> if needed.</li>\n \t<li>EPICS worker Updates the SIGNED field on the LISAN screen with the date the payment agreement was signed by the CSRU worker.</li>\n</ol>\nCASE REVIEWS:\n\nWhen completing a Case Review, check CASESTAT for open LISAN and Contempt screens. Also review narratives and PAYHIST. Send a referral to EPICS if a noncompliance has been issued and payments are being received or to legal if contempt and legal has requested notification.\";i:1582639597597;s:25099:\"<b>Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b>Can form 470-3274, Certificate Of Noncompliance, be faxed to the licensing agency to expedite the process?\n<b>A.</b>Listed below are the appropriate methods of sending license sanction forms to the following agencies:\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>Department of Transportation (DOT)</b> -- Do <i><b>not</b></i> FAX forms or send forms through regular mail to DOT. All sanctions and withdrawals are processed electronically through ICAR.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Natural Resources (DNR)</b> -- FAX forms to DNR; do not send through regular mail. E-mail information regarding withdrawals to <a href=\"mailto:csrupolicy-enforcement@dhs.state.ia.us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>CSRU Policy Enforcement</b></a>.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Public Health (DPH)</b> -- E-mail forms to DPH to <a href=\"mailto:beth.jorgenson@idph.iowa.gov\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>Beth Jorgenson</b></a> and enter in the subject line: CSRU, {payor last name, payor first name}, {ICAR case #}\nExample: CSRU: Smith, John, #11111 Do not send forms through regular mail.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Commerce (DOC)</b> -- FAX forms to DOC. Do not send forms through regular mail.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Inspections and Appeals (DIA)</b> -- FAX forms to DIA. Do not send forms through regular mail.</li>\n \t<li><b>Department of Public Safety (DPS)</b> -- FAX forms to DPS. Do not send forms through regular mail.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Contempt</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> If the obligor has two cases with court orders filed in the same county/judicial district, one referred for license sanction and the other for contempt, do I proceed with the license sanction for the case not referred for contempt?\n<b>A.</b> In general, to prevent the risk of double-jeopardy, it is advisable <i>not</i> to proceed with the license sanction; however, if the contempt hearing has <i>not</i> been set, you may retract the contempt referral and proceed with the license sanction, if appropriate.\n\nIf the contempt hearing <i>has</i> been set, discuss the case with your unit attorney as to how to proceed.\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can I proceed with a license sanction and contempt at the same time?\n<b>A.</b> No. Per Iowa Administrative Code*, contempt is an exemption from the license sanction process. You must withdraw the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> (if issued) and process-end the LISAN screen before proceeding with a contempt action.\n\n*IAC 441- 98.102(6) <i>Contempt process</i>. Involvement in a contempt action dealing with support issues is considered a valid reason for exemption from the license sanction process during the pendency of the contempt action.\n\n<b>Q.</b> The obligor does not have a valid license or vehicle registration. Do I have to wait 90 days after we stop the license sanction process before pursuing a contempt action?\n<b>A.</b> You may end the license sanction process if you determine that the obligor no longer has any valid licenses or vehicle registrations. You may then consult with your office attorney for a possible contempt referral.\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can I pursue a license sanction and contempt on an obligor who has multiple cases in two different offices?\n<b>A.</b> You may pursue license sanction and contempt on an obligor with multiple cases in two different offices. The cases must have different court orders and you may not pursue both actions on the same case.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>District Court Hearing</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> If the obligor requests a district court hearing, should I issue the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>?\n<b>A.</b> No, do not issue the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>. The clerk of court will inform the licensing agency that a court hearing has been requested. The licensing agency will then take the appropriate steps in regards to the sanction.\n\n<b>Q.</b> What if the obligor requests a district court hearing at the time of the license sanction conference and the Certificate of Noncompliance has not been issued? What should I do?\n<b>A.</b> Consult with your office attorney. The attorney may wish to file a resistance.\n\n<b>Q.</b> What if the obligor sends a written request for a district court hearing to the local office? Should I forward the request to the clerk of court\'\'s office?\n<b>A.</b> The payor must file a request for hearing with the clerk of court. If the payor sends a request directly to CSRU, contact the payor and explain he/she must file the request for hearing with the clerk of court in the county where the order is filed.\n\nIf EPICS receives a request for hearing directly from the payor, send an email to the CSRUOffice Mailbox with a \"cc\" to the supervisor advising of the request for hearing. CSRU will follow-up by contacting the payor (see also: <a href=\"http://dhssp/csr/Central/epics/LISAN%20BPH/34-District%20Court%20Hearing.docx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/sharepoint.png\" /> District Court Hearing</b></a>)\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Driver\'\'s Licenses</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> The obligor\'\'s driver\'\'s license is currently barred and there is no matching vehicle registration. What purpose does it serve to sanction the obligor\'\'s license for child support?\n<b>A.</b> According to DOT, you should not be concerned with what other sanctions an obligor has on his or her driving record. The other sanction may be lifted at any time. In order for the child support sanction to become effective, the sanction needs to be on the record at the time the other sanction is lifted. Although there is no guarantee that the obligor will ever again be eligible to receive an Iowa driver\'\'s license, there is no harm in placing the sanction.\n\n<b>Q.</b>The obligor\'\'s Iowa driver\'\'s license is still valid and the obligor has moved to another state. Should I still sanction the license?\n<b>A.</b> A driver\'\'s license \"stop\" entered in Iowa is placed on a national database which other states <i>may</i> access prior to issuing a driver\'\'s license. According to DOT, it is <i>assumed</i> that states would not issue a driver\'\'s license to a person if the person had sanctions in another state; however, each state has its own exceptions to that assumption. Again, while there is no guarantee that a child support sanction in Iowa will prevent an obligor from obtaining a driver\'\'s license in another state, there is no harm in placing the sanction.\n\n<b>Q.</b> What does Ã¢â‚¬Å“OTHÃ¢â‚¬Â mean as an entry on DLIC in the non-cdl stat field?\n<b>A.</b> According to DOT it means that a prior sanction has been lifted. The obligor does not have a valid license at this time, and the obligor is eligible for a license should the obligor apply.\n\n<b>Q.</b> What does it mean when the cdl-status and non-cdl stat fields on DLIC are blank, and the license is not listed as a class Ã¢â‚¬Å“0Ã¢â‚¬Â (ID-only)?\n<b>A.</b> It could mean that it is an Ã¢â‚¬Å“NDLÃ¢â‚¬Â (no driverÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s license) record. This means that the court has issued a ticket or fine and the person did not have a driverÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s license at the time. DOT issues the NDL record so that if the person attempts to obtain a driverÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s license at a later date, DOT will be aware that there is a fine or ticket that needs to be paid.\n\n<b>Q.</b> The obligor was in the office today and paid his/her delinquency. I issued the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to DOT. Can I give the obligor a copy of the withdrawal to take with him/her directly to the DOT office?\n<b>A.</b> You may provide the obligor a copy of the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>; however, the obligor may <i>not</i> take the withdrawal directly to the DOT office to obtain his/her driver\'\'s license. The reason this is not possible is due to DOT\'\'s requirements for reinstating a driver\'\'s license.\n\nWhen you generate the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, ICAR sends an electronic withdrawal transaction to DOT\'\'s computer system. DOT\'\'s system processes this transaction that same night though a batch program. When the sanction is removed from DOT\'\'s system, DOT generates a \"lift notice\" to the obligor explaining that the sanction is lifted and the obligor may now obtain his/her driver\'\'s license. DOT\'\'s system does not generate the lift notice until the <i>following</i> day after the withdrawal transaction is processed. Once the lift notice generates, the notice is available online to DOT before it is mailed.\n\nDOT will not reinstate a license for an obligor without the obligor having his/her DOT lift notice in-hand. This means that the obligor must wait until he/she receives the lift notice in the mail before attempting to obtain his/her license at a DOT office. DOT has confirmed that if an obligor has obtained a withdrawal and does not have a copy of the lift notice, and the lift notice is available to DOT online, DOT will print the lift notice for the obligor and reinstate the obligor\'\'s license.\n\nTherefore, it is important to emphasize to the obligor that even thought he/she has obtained a withdrawal from CSRU, the obligor must wait until he/she receives notice from DOT regarding reinstatement of the driver\'\'s license before attempting to obtain his/her license at a DOT office.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Exemptions</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> For an obligor to enter vocational rehab, the obligor must prove that he/she has a disability. If I determine that the obligor is in vocational rehab, do I still need a <i>Physician\'\'s Statement</i> as proof of disability?\n<b>A.</b> Yes, you should still obtain a <i>Physician\'\'s Statement</i> from the obligor.\n\n<b>Q.</b> Social security retirement is considered an exemption from the license sanction process. Should I link SSA to the IWO and process-end the LISAN screen if I verify the obligor is receiving social security retirement benefits?\n<b>A.</b> Link SSA to the IWO and enter a Ã¢â‚¬Å“YÃ¢â‚¬Â in the ssr field on the FEDBEN screen if not already entered. This will prevent the case from selecting for license sanction. You may then process-end the LISAN screen.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Forms</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> When generating license sanction forms through the FORMVIEW screen, can I replace the system-entered phone number with my direct phone number?\n<b>A.</b> Yes. You may enter your direct phone number over the existing phone number in the CSRU TELEPHONE NUMBER field on the FORMVIEW screen and update the form. After ICAR generates the form, narrate that you provided the obligor with your direct phone number.\n\n<b>Q.</b>The obligor has multiple cases and the IWO payments are split between the cases. Due to the split, the IWO payments being received on the case are lower than the IWO amount. These payments are also lower than the payment agreement amount. Does the obligor need to make up the difference between the IWO payments and the payment agreement amount?\n<b>A.</b> No. The obligor does not need to make up any difference between the IWO amounts and the payment agreement amount.\n\n<b>Q.</b> The obligor has multiple cases and all of the IWO payments are being paid toward current support on another of the obligor\'\'s cases. Can I send a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> since no payments are being received on the case with the license sanction payment agreement?\n<b>A.</b> No. Payments are being received from the income provider and are being split according to IWODIST. Do <i>not</i> send the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> when IWO payments are being received from the income provider on at least one of the obligor\'\'s cases.\n\n<b>Q.</b> Should I proceed with a license sanction when an IWO has been sent to a temp agency?\n<b>A.</b> Call the temp agency to verify if the obligor will be given any assignments. If the answer is no, unlink the temp agency from the IWO so that the case may select for license sanction.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Levy</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can I proceed with a license sanction and an administrative levy at the same time?\n<b>A.</b> Yes. A license sanction can be initiated when there is a pending administrative levy. However, if the obligor has signed a payment agreement and is in compliance with the payment agreement, proceed with caution before a new administrative levy is initiated. Verify the balance of the account(s) and discuss the case circumstances with your supervisor.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>License Sanction Conference</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can an obligor request another conference, even after a conference has been rescheduled (2nd conference) and held?\n<b>A.</b> You cannot deny the obligor\'\'s request for a conference. If the obligor fails to attend a rescheduled conference, issue the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> (if not previously issued). If the obligor requests another conference, grant the request and schedule another conference.\n\n<b>Q.</b> If form 470-3274, <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, is issued because the obligor is not in compliance with the license sanction payment agreement, can the obligor request a conference?\n<b>A.</b> If the payor has already had a license sanction conference and has an existing License Sanction Payment Agreement, the payor will not be given another license sanction conference. The payor must make up all missed payments from the License Sanction Payment Agreement, pay all past-due support, or apply for a district court hearing.\n\n<b>Q.</b> The obligor has two cases in two different offices. The obligor requests a conference with one office, but lives closer to the other office. Which office should handle the conference?\n<b>A.</b> Ask the obligor at which office the obligor would like to have the conference. The obligor must make the decision as to where he/she would like the conference to be held. See PIF <a href=\"file://hoovr3s2/csru.772/CSTMWRK/PITCREWS/SPECENF/PIFS/Resolved/License%20Sanction/2003\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/folder.png\" /> LS02-03</b></a> revised for more information.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>License Sanction Criteria</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> Is a current child support obligation required to proceed with a license sanction?\n<b>A.</b> No. A current child support obligation is not required to proceed.\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can a license sanction be pursued on a case where the current support obligation has not been ended but there is currently a suspension of current support in place?\n<b>A.</b> Verify there is <i>not</i> a \"C\" (current) or \"F\" (future) in the S (SUSPENSE) field for the obligation on the OBLIGHST screen. When the entry is \"C\" or \"F\", and the child is residing with the obligor, carefully review the case circumstances and schedule an administrative enforcement conference before proceeding to the next step. Consult with your supervisor if you think a conference is not appropriate. Do <i>not</i> proceed with a license sanction action without supervisory approval.\n\n<b>Q.</b> I think I have a good case for license sanction but no LISAN screen has been built. What do I do?\n<b>A.</b> ICAR only builds a LISAN screen when a case meets license sanction criteria, and the obligor matches with a license.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Process - Ending a License Sanction</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can the obligee request the license sanction be ended? There is no danger to the obligee or the children; the obligee just doesn’t feel it is a good time to proceed.\n<b>A.</b> If CSRU is providing enforcement, the license sanction cannot be ended because of the obligee\'\'s request.\n\n<b>Q.</b> If a license sanction was initiated and then the child emancipates causing the current support obligation to end, should the license sanction be ended?\n<b>A.</b> A current support obligation is no longer required for the license sanction process. Continue with the license sanction process until the support owed or some other criteria for ending the process is met.\n\n<b>Q.</b> If a license sanction is active and a notice of bankruptcy is received, should the license sanction process be ended?\n<b>A.</b> If you receive notice of ANY bankruptcy action, issue form 470-3275, <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, to the licensing agency. Because a Chapter 7 bankruptcy is of short duration and due to the possibility of sanctions against CSRU, it is recommended that you wait until the plan is dismissed or discharged before continuing license sanction proceedings. For more information on bankruptcy, see <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/11-G.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> EM 11-G, License Sanction</b></a>.\n\n<b>Q.</b> If at least six months have passed since the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i> was mailed/served, when should I process-end the LISAN screen?\n<b>A.</b> Process-end the LISAN screen when:\n<ul>\n \t<li>At least six months have passed since you sent form 470-3278, <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i>,</li>\n \t<li>The payment agreement is not signed, and</li>\n \t<li>The obligor is not sanctioned.</li>\n</ul>\nExample:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Jan 04 - You send the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i>.</li>\n \t<li>Feb 04 - The obligor <i>does not sign</i> a proposed payment agreement for $50 per month.</li>\n \t<li>Mar 04 - The obligor begins making payments of $50 per month.</li>\n \t<li>Apr 04 - Payment for $50 is credited.</li>\n \t<li>May 04 - Payment for $50 is credited.</li>\n \t<li>June 04 - Payment for $50 is credited.</li>\n \t<li>July 04 - Payment for $50 is credited.</li>\n \t<li>Aug 04 - The obligor stops making payments.</li>\n</ul>\nNo payment is received in August. Because at least six months have passed since the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i> was mailed/served, process-end the LISAN screen with the code Ã¢â‚¬Å“OTHÃ¢â‚¬Â. Wait for ICAR to again select the case for license sanction and reinitiate the license sanction process. If it has been six months since the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i> was mailed/served, we need to again mail it to/serve it on the obligor. This reduces the likelihood of the obligor believing we have waived our intent to proceed with a license sanction.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>REG Payments</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> When a case is receiving REG payments and they are below the obligation level, may I pursue license sanction?\n<b>A.</b> When the obligor is making REG payments and the payments are not equal to or greater than the obligation amount for three months, ICAR selects the case for license sanction as long as the case meets all other license sanction criteria. However, if the obligor is making consistent payments and those payments are below the obligation level, you may want to consult with your supervisor before proceeding with a license sanction.\n\n<b>Q.</b> I received LISAN calendar flag (LISAN 33) starting the obligor has made REG payments equal to or greater than the obligation amount for the last three months (this may be several payments or could be a single, large payment) and to send the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>. Should I send the withdrawal even though the obligor has not signed a payment agreement, paid the support owed, or provided proof of a valid exemption?\n<b>A.</b> Review the case circumstances. You may want to call the obligor and encourage the obligor to sign a payment agreement. Issue the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i> when you and your supervisor feel it is appropriate.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Service of the Obligor</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can the obligor be served with the <i>Official Notice of Potential License Sanction</i> if the obligor comes to the local office? If the obligor is served at the local office, should the obligor sign a waiver of personal service?\n<b>A.</b> Yes, the obligor may be served if the obligor comes to the local office. The obligor should sign a waiver of personal service so there is no question that the obligor was served.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Updating the LISAN screen</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> I made separate entries in multiple fields on the LISAN screen and pressed F3 twice to update the screen. ICAR did not issue/delete the corresponding calendar flags and narratives. Why?&lt;/br /&gt;\n<b>A.</b> When you enter data in multiple non-related fields, you must press F3 twice after each separate entry. This ensures ICAR processes the entries correctly and issues/deletes all related narratives and calendar flags.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Vehicle Registration</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> Can I prevent an obligor from renewing the registration on a leased vehicle?\n<b>A.</b> You cannot place a vehicle registration sanction on a leased vehicle because the leasing company, not the obligor, owns it.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</b>\n\n<b>Q.</b> If the payor has a LISAN payment agreement, is currently sanctioned, and wants to regain his/her licenses and/or vehicle registrations, what must the payor do before I can issue the <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>?\n<b>A.</b> The payor needs to pay all payments that were missed since the LISAN payment agreement start date.\n\nExample: The license sanction payment agreement is $75/month. The IWO is $100/month.\n<ul>\n \t<li>Jan 04 - IWO payment for $50 is posted with a receipt credited date in January.</li>\n \t<li>Feb 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in Feb.</li>\n \t<li>Mar 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in Mar.</li>\n \t<li>Apr 04 - IWO payment for $75 is posted with a receipt credited date in Apr.</li>\n \t<li>May 04 - IWO is disconnected. IWO payment for $75 is posted with a receipt credited date in May.</li>\n \t<li>June 04 - Last IWO payment for $25 is posted with a receipt credited date in June.</li>\n \t<li>July 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in July.</li>\n \t<li>Aug 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in Aug.</li>\n \t<li>Sep 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in Sept.</li>\n</ul>\nIt is September 2004. The obligor needs to make payments for the months of July, August and September*.\n\nExample: The license sanction payment agreement is $50/month. The IWO is $50/month.\n<ul>\n \t<li>Jan 04 - Payment agreement payment for $50 is posted with a receipt credited date in Jan.</li>\n \t<li>Feb 04 - Payment agreement payment for $25 is posted with a receipt credited date in Feb.</li>\n \t<li>Mar 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in Mar.</li>\n \t<li>Apr 04 - IWO payment for $50 is posted with a receipt credited date in Apr.</li>\n \t<li>May 04 - IWO is disconnected. IWO payment for $50 is posted with a receipt credited date in May.</li>\n \t<li>June 04 - Last IWO payment for $25 is posted with a receipt credited date in June.</li>\n \t<li>July 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in July.</li>\n \t<li>Aug 04 - Payment agreement payment for $50 is posted with a receipt credited date in Aug.</li>\n \t<li>Sep 04 - No payment is posted with a receipt credited date in Sep.</li>\n</ul>\nIt is September 2004. The obligor needs to make payments for the months of July and September*.\n\n*A payor must catch up all missed payments before a Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance will be issued. When there is a LISAN payment agreement in place, we must have the LISAN payment agreement amount paid by a REG payment each month. NOTE: If a MIW, IWO, or UIB payment is received in a month, the payor is not required to also make a REG payment in that same month.\n\n<b>Q.</b> If the payor <b>does not have a LISAN payment agreement</b>, is currently sanctioned, and wants to regain his/her licenses and/or vehicle registrations, what must the payor do before I can issue the Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance?\n<b>A.</b> The payor has four options:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Pay all arrears and current support due (pay case to zero), or</li>\n \t<li>Provide income provider information (must be verified), or</li>\n \t<li>Provide exemption information (must be verified), or</li>\n \t<li>Request a conference, attend the conference, and follow through with the requirements from the conference</li>\n</ul>\nThe worker must verify employment, verify the exemption, or schedule &amp; hold a conference. If a payor submits a request for a conference in writing, the worker must send and receive financial statements/documentation, verify that financial information, hold the conference, and then issue the decision. If the decision of the conference is to set up a license sanction payment agreement, the payor must return the signed payment agreement with the first payment before a Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance will be issued.\";}"
