                     "meta_value": {
                        "__cdata": "a:6:{i:1582830794867;s:6173:\"<p><b>DLIC License</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Class field indicates the type of driver’s license:\n<ul>\n<li>“A” = Commercial driver’s license (CDL) - Semi-truck license</li>\n<li>“B” = Commercial driver’s license (CDL) - Large vehicle license</li>\n<li>“C” = Standard non-commercial driver’s license; or a CDL when there is an entry in the <b>Endorsement (ENDOR)</b> field.</li>\n<li>“D” = Chauffeur’s license</li>\n<li>“M” = Motorcycle license</li>\n<li>“0” = Identification-only (no license). Displays as an “I” in the DLIC CLASS field on LISAN screen.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>The <b>Issue Date (ISSDT)</b> field displays the date the license was issued.</li>\n<li>The <b>Expiration Date (EXPDT)</b> field displays the date the license expires.</li>\n<li>The <b>CDL-Status</b> field indicates the current status of the person’s CDL license.</li>\n<li>The <b>Non-CDL Status</b> field indicates the current status of the person’s non-commercial license.</li>\n<li>The <b>Process Date (PROCDT)</b> field displays the date the person’s record was last updated. \n<p style=\"color: red;\"><b>Note:</b> This may be -<br />\n<ul style=\"color: red;\">\n<li>the date information displayed on the screen, such as the address or CDL/Non-CDL Status fields, was last updated;</li>\n<li>the date a ticket or violation was added or removed (not viewable);</li>\n<li>or the date DOT\'s quarterly \"purge\" program ran against the DLIC database.</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Codes</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>BAR - Barred</li>\n<li>Blank - None</li>\n<li>DED - Deceased</li>\n<li>DEN - Denied</li>\n<li>DIS - Disqualified</li>\n<li>EXP - Expired</li>\n<li>OTH - Other not valid</li>\n<li>REV - Revoked</li>\n<li>SUR - Surrendered</li>\n<li>SUS - Suspended</li>\n<li>TRL - Temporary Restricted License</li>\n<li>VAL - Valid</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<p><b>Vehicle Registration</b></p>\n<p>To view an obligor\'s vehicle registration, use the VRT (Vehicle Registration and Titling) system.</p>\n<p><b><span style=\"color: red;\">VRT</span> Fields</b></p>\n<p>The <span style=\"color: red;\"><b>Start</b></span> date is the date that <span style=\"color: red;\">the vehicle registration is effective</span>.</p>\n<p>The <span style=\"color: red;\"><b>End</b></span> date is the <span style=\"color: red;\">date</span> that the registration is up for renewal (<span style=\"color: red;\">expires</span>).</p>\n<p>The <span style=\"color: red;\"><b>Customer Type</b></span> indicates whether the owner is an individual or a business. <span style=\"color: red;\">This field displays \"individual\" when the vehicle is registered to a person, or \"organization\" when the vehicle is registered to a business</span>. ICAR does not load information on vehicles registered to a business, even if the vehicle is registered in the obligor’s name and the business is a sole proprietorship. This is because we cannot sanction the registration of a vehicle owned by a business. We also cannot sanction the registration of a leased vehicle.</p>\n<p><b>Initial Agency Datamatch Report</b></p>\n<p>Previously, when a vehicle registration contained a status code (e.g. \"17\" indicated junking certificate issued for this vehicle), the veh reg stat field on the monthly <i>Initial Agency Datamatch</i> report displayed \"17\".</p>\n<p>Now, when a vehicle registration contains any type of status code, the veh reg stat field on the monthly <i>Initial Agency Datamatch</i> report displays \"AA.\"  When the vehicle registration contains no status code (meaning the registration is valid), the veh reg stat field displays a blank.  This is because we no longer receive vehicle registration status code information from DOT.</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>You may proceed with a license sanction even when:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The payor resides out of state</li>\n<li>The payor’s driver’s license is already listed as suspended, revoked, etc., or is expired</li>\n<li>There is a match with a vehicle registration and you are unable to locate the payor\'s on VRHQ, or the registration is not “valid”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>DOT Info</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>DOT maintains a database for drivers’ licenses and vehicle registrations.</li>\n<li>When DOT receives a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, they enter a <i>pending</i> sanction on the drivers’ license database and send the payor a pre-sanction notice. This sanction is against the payor’s <i>driving privileges</i>, which means current and future driver’s licenses and current and future vehicle registrations.</li>\n<li>After 35 days from the date DOT sends their notice, DOT’s automated system changes the pending sanction to a <i>suspense</i> or “stop,” unless you issue a <i>Notice of Withdrawal of Certificate of Noncompliance</i>. The “stop” is also placed on the vehicle registration file based on the payor’s SSN. This allows DOT to sanction the registrations of <b>all</b> vehicles registered under the payor’s name.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Sending Info to DOT</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>ICAR interfaces electronically with DOT’s licensing database. When you enter a date in the gen cert of noncom field on the LISAN screen for a case, ICAR creates and sends a “stop” record to DOT. Similarly, when you enter a date in the gen withdrawal of noncom field for a case, ICAR creates and sends a “withdrawal” record to DOT.</li>\n<li>DOT processes the “stops” and “withdrawals” on a per-case basis. If a payor has more than one case, DOT places a “stop” on the payor’s record for each case having a <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> sent to DOT. Similarly, if there are multiple “stops” on the payor’s record, the payor’s driving privileges will not be restored until <b>all</b> “stops” are withdrawn for all cases.</li>\n<li>The certificate of mailing on the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> was changed to reflect that you are no longer sending an actual copy of the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i> to DOT.</li>\n<li>If you make an error in generating the <i>Certificate of Noncompliance</i>, entering a date in the gen withdrawal of noncom field on the <i>same day</i> cancels the transaction to DOT.</li>\n</ul>\";i:1582830799055;s:272:\"<p><b>DEER</b> - Deer Hunting License</p>\n<p><b>FISH</b> - Fishing License</p>\n<p><b>HUNT</b> - Hunting License (other than deer or turkey)</p>\n<p><b>TURK</b> - Turkey Hunting License</p>\n<p><b>MISC</b> - Miscellaneous licenses like Ginseng growers and cultivators</p>\";i:1582830799493;s:23:\"[ninja_tables id=\"961\"]\";i:1582830799871;s:245:\"<p><b>ACCL</b> - Cert. Public Accountant/Accounting Practioner</p>\n<p><b>ENGX</b> - Engineers / Surveyors</p>\n<p><b>INS</b> - Insurance Agents</p>\n<p><b>REAL</b> - Real Estate Brokers / Sellers</p>\n<p><b>REAP</b> - Real Estate Appraisers</p>\";i:1582830800356;s:109:\"<p><b>GAME</b> - Employees of casinos, racetracks and riverboats (except for employees of a reservation).</p>\";i:1582830800877;s:102:\"<p><b>PRVT</b> - Private investigators, private security employees and bail enforcement employees.</p>\";}"
