                        "__cdata": "a:19:{i:1584373585689;s:822:\"<b>Information about offenders in community-based corrections and prisoners:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Names (including aliases)</li>\n \t<li>SSNs (including aliases)</li>\n \t<li>Birth dates and locations (including aliases)</li>\n \t<li>Addresses (old and current)</li>\n \t<li>Employers’ names, addresses, and phone numbers, as well as job data (old and current)</li>\n \t<li>Education</li>\n \t<li>Physical identifiers</li>\n \t<li>Offenses and corrections status</li>\n \t<li>Case managers names and phone numbers</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Additional information about prisoners:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Where currently incarcerated</li>\n \t<li>If working while incarcerated</li>\n \t<li>Discharge dates</li>\n \t<li>Board of Parole review dates</li>\n \t<li>Banking Information</li>\n \t<li>Prisoner Movements</li>\n \t<li>Prisoner Transfers</li>\n</ul>\";i:1584373586473;s:524:\"Refer to the <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Location/Contents/NonAutoLocate/ICON/ICON%20Quick%20Reference%20Guide%20Updated%2003.11.05.doc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> <b>ICON/Department of Corrections Quick Reference Guide</b></a>.\n\nThis document provides:\n<ul>\n \t<li>how to access/log onto ICON</li>\n \t<li>central office support for ICON</li>\n \t<li>general questions and answers about ICON</li>\n</ul>\";i:1584373586817;s:476:\"You may use the ICON website to locate any party in a case for child support recovery purposes. Do not use it for personal reasons such as looking up yourself, friends or relatives.\nFor more information on the correct use of CSRU tools, refer to <a href=\"http://dhs.iowa.gov/sites/default/files/9-a.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/pdf.png\" /> <b>GENERAL PROGRAM INFORMATION, 9-A</b></a>.\";i:1584373587105;s:464:\"<b>You may access the ICON website from using this link:</b>\n\n<a href=\"https://iadoc-casemgmt.doc.gov.state.ia.us/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://iadoc-casemgmt.doc.gov.state.ia.us/</a> (broken link\n\n<b>To login to ICON enter your:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>User Name:</b> In format of <i>firstname.lastname.</i></li>\n \t<li><b>Password:</b> Unique to ICON &amp; case-sensitive.</li>\n</ul>\nYour supervisor will determine if you should have access to ICON.\";i:1584373587384;s:1069:\"<b>Printing</b>\n\nTo print the information shown on a screen, right click anywhere within the screen and then click on print.\n\n<b>Copy/Paste</b>\n\nYou cannot copy from another application and paste into ICON. For example, you cannot copy the offender number from ICAR and paste it into the offender number field.\n\nYou can copy some information from ICON and paste it into another application. For example, you can copy an address from ICON and paste it into a Word document. You cannot copy the entry in the offender number field from ICON and paste it into a Word document.\n\n<b>ACDS and ICBC</b>\n\nACDS was the DOC database for prisoner records prior to October 1, 2004 when these records were moved to the ICON website.\n\nICBC was the DOC database for community-based offender records prior to August 2000 when the ICON website was created.\n\n<b>A few “DO NOT”s:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Do not use your browser’s <b>back</b> button to navigate the website.</li>\n \t<li>Do not use the MAINTENANCE option on the <b>MENU</b>. This is for DOC staff.</li>\n</ul>\";i:1584373587665;s:398:\"The ICON MENU has 4 options: Offender, Reports, Maintenance, and System. Move the cursor to one of the options and it will bring up a secondary MENU options.\n\nFor example, to display the PASSWORD summary screen, first click on SYSTEM and then click on SECURITY and then PASSWORD.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/OldNewConfirmPassword.png\" />\";i:1584373587930;s:731:\"The OFFENDER NUMBER appears at the top of the screen.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/OffenderNumber.png\" />\n\nIf you know the offender number, type it in the offender number field and press the key with the face on it. If you don\'\'t know the offender number, press the spyglass key.\n\nOffender numbers are 7-digits long. Numbers cannot be copied from another application and pasted into the offender number field.\n\nWhen you enter an offender number ICON displays the offender’s name on file with the DOC as a non-alias.\n\nEven though the DOC is not currently supervising the person you may be able to find birth, address, employer and other useful information on ICON.\";i:1584373588193;s:2709:\"The <a><b><i>OFFENDER INFORMATION</i></b></a> screen displays the prison facility and housing unit where the offender is incarcerated; the room and bed numbers; and his or her privilege level. ICAR will load the prison as an address for the person during the AutoLocate process. When you add a prison as an address for either the payor or payee, use the <a><b><i>proper format for prison addresses</i></b></a>.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/OffenderInformation.png\" />\n\nRemember to follow the <a><b><i>Special Handling Requirements</i></b></a> according to the Protocol for Changing Personal Information when updating a payee’s address to or from a prison address.\n\nThe OFFENDER INFORMATION screen will also display the start date for the housing information and the person’s work assignments.\n\nOffenders entering prison are sent to Oakdale (IMCC) for classification. The statewide privilege level field will read “Reception” if the inmate is being classified. Do not add Oakdale as a verified employer when they have a “Reception” privilege level because the inmate is not working during this time. The statewide privilege level field will read “General Population” if the prisoner is assigned to serve his or her sentence at Oakdale. Work assignments are located under <a><b><i>Work Assignments</i></b></a>.\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>Prison:</b> The majority of inmates have this supervision status.</li>\n \t<li><b>Prison Compact:</b> Iowa is housing the inmate for another state. That state will usually take one of our prisoners in return.</li>\n \t<li><b>Prison Safekeeper:</b> Federal inmates housed at the prison in Newton.</li>\n</ul>\n<b>TDD:</b> Tentative Discharge Date. This is the expected date the person will be discharged from prison. This date can be changed based upon an offender’s behavior or other circumstances. An entry of “LIFE” in this field means the person is serving a life sentence.\n\n<b>MPD:</b> Minimum Parole Date. This is the earliest the person will be paroled. There is only a date in this field if the person is subject to mandatory sentencing laws.\n\n<b>CL:</b> Custody Level. An offender is sent to Oakdale (IMCC) for classification when he or she enters the prison system. The prisoner is assigned a maximum, medium or minimum custody level at this time.\n\nThe OFFENDER INFORMATION screen will also display the offender’s work unit and case manager’s name.\n\nThe alerts field may display other information regarding the person’s supervision status. It will be completed if an Iowa inmate is being housed by another state. It will display “Escaped” if the inmate escaped from prison.\";i:1584373588480;s:4555:\"Under the OFFENDER pull down menu, click on the Movement or Transfer items and it will display the start date for the person to report to the facility. Click <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Establishment/Contents/Appendix/Vocational%20Rehab.doc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/02/word.png\" /> <b>here</b></a> to display a list of Residential Facility addresses provided by the Department of Corrections.\n\nIf the offender’s Supervision Status is “Work Release” or “OWI Continuum”, the person is residing at the facility listed in the field. DOC staff often updates the offender’s current address to reflect the facility address.\n\nThe Supervision Status section of the OFFENDER INFORMATION screen describes the person’s legal status with the DOC. It will display “OWI Continuum”, “Probation”, “Parole”, “Work Release” or other descriptor to show the person is currently in community-based corrections.\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>OWI Continuum:</b> An offender has a third OWI conviction. The person lives at a supervised treatment facility for 3-6 months. The offender typically does not work while they are at the facility.</li>\n \t<li><b>Parole:</b> An offender has served part of the sentence in prison and is serving the remainder of their sentence in community-based corrections. He or she can be revoked to prison for not complying with the terms of their parole.</li>\n</ul>\nParolees generally do not live in a supervised facility. When they do, it is usually only for a few days because they do not have anywhere else to stay.\n\nIf an offender serves their full sentence in prison, the person is not on parole and is not supervised by the DOC when they are released.\n\n<b>Probation:</b> An offender is sentenced to prison but has not been incarcerated or their sentenced was changed to probation within 90 days of becoming incarcerated (shock probation). The prison sentence is suspended and the person is serving their time in community-based corrections.\n\nOffenders on probation may or may not be living in a supervised facility, commonly referred to as a “halfway house”.\n\nAn offender can be revoked to prison for not complying with the terms of their probation.\n\n<b>Work Release:</b> An offender has been released from prison and is living in a supervised facility. The offender is allowed to leave the facility to go to work in the community. If the offender successfully completes the work release program, they are allowed to return home. If they are not successful, they can be revoked to prison.\n\n<b>TDD:</b> Tentative Discharge Date. This field displays only if the person is on parole. It is the last day the Department of Corrections can keep the person on parole.\n\n<b>SDD:</b> Supervision Discharge Date. This field displays if the person is not on parole. It is the expected date the person will be discharged from supervision. For example, the date the person is expected to successfully complete probation.\n\n<b>LOS:</b> Level of Supervision.\n<ul>\n \t<li><b>Low or Minimum Risk:</b> The offender’s employment and address information may or may not be current. The DOC is not required to maintain address and employment records for these offenders because the case manager’s caseload is approximately 1100 people.</li>\n \t<li><b>Administrative:</b> The offender’s address and employment information may or may not be current. This status is used for people who cannot report to their case manager. For example, the person is a truck driver, an escapee or in jail.</li>\n</ul>\nTo see the charges for which the offender is currently being supervised and other details, click on OFFENDER INFORMATION. This screen displays the offender’s work unit and case manager’s name.\n\nThe Supervision Modifier and specialties fields show additional information about the offender’s supervision status.\n<ul>\n \t<li>Polk County Jail inmates housed at Newton and Mitchellville due to overcrowding will show Newton and Mitchellville in the Housing field. Other offenders in jail will also show an “In Jail” Supervision Modifier.</li>\n \t<li>The Violator Program is a person’s last chance before being revoked to prison. These are intensive six-month programs held at the Fort Dodge, Newton, Luster Heights, and Mitchellville facilities. Offenders cannot work while they are in the program. The specialties field will display “Violator Program” if an offender is in this program.</li>\n</ul>\";i:1584373588752;s:1439:\"If you do not know the offender number, click on the <b>SEARCH</b> icon to the right of the offender number field. The OFFENDER SEARCH screen will be displayed.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/search.png\" />\n\nIn the search Options section select \"Offender Information\" from the first drop down box. In the second drop down box, select \"Full\".\n\nType in the person’s name (First, Middle, Last) or social security number in the appropriate fields and click on the search button.\n\n<hr />\n\n<b>SEARCH RESULTS</b>\n\nA list of offenders matching the search criteria will be displayed in a frame at the bottom of the OFFENDER SEARCH screen. ICON will display the number of records returned in the first line of the frame.\n\nScroll through the frame to see all of the matching records.\n\nEach record displays the offender number, name, social security number, and date of birth.\n\nNames, social security numbers or dates of birth recorded as an alias with the DOC are shown in italics.\n\nThe screen will display the date the photograph was taken. It will also display the offender’s height, weight and other identifying information.\n\nTo load the person’s offender number and return to the OFFENDER FRAME, click on the button to the left of the person’s offender number in the OFFENDER SEARCH results screen.\n\nThen click on the select button at the bottom of the screen.\";i:1584373589016;s:936:\"You can easily access ICON records for offenders in your CSRU caseload by storing them in the MY OFFENDERS screen.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/MyOffender.png\" />\n\nFrom the main ICON screen, enter an offender number in the offender number: field, then click on the <b>My Offenders</b> icon.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/MainIconScreen.png\" />\n\nTo add the offender that is currently displayed in the OFFENDER FRAME to the MY OFFENDERS screen, click on the <b>add</b> button in the MY OFFENDERS screen.\n\nTo remove an offender stored in the MY OFFENDERS screen, click on the <b>remove</b> button at the top of the page.\n\nTo display the OFFENDER FRAME for another person in the MY OFFENDERS screen, click on the button to the left of their name and then click on the <b>select</b> button at the bottom of the screen.\";i:1584373589280;s:282:\"The case manager’s name is displayed on the OFFENDER INFORMATION screen. The case manager’s work location, phone number, fax number or email address, are listed.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/OffenderInformation-1.png\" />\";i:1584373589552;s:695:\"Access the OFFENDER pull down menu to display the CORE OFFENDER INFORMATION. Click on A-D and then Address Information. See example below.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/AddressInformation.png\" />\n\nThis screen displays the offender’s address history.\n\nThe offender’s current address displays a date in the end date field. Consider employer and address information unverified for community-based offenders. See <a><b><i>How do I manually Verify Employment and Address Information?</i></b></a>.\n\nThe forwarding field will display “Yes” if the prison has a forwarding address for someone who is about to be released from prison.\";i:1584373589800;s:1047:\"Access the OFFENDER pull down menu to display the CORE OFFENDER INFORMATION. Click on E-M and then Employment Information. See example below.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/EmploymentInformation.png\" />\n\nThis screen displays an offender’s work history. Reasons why an offender is not working include “disabled”, “retired”, “unemployed” and “welfare”. Use this screen to see where someone in community-based corrections is working. (Use the OFFENDER INFORMATION screen to see if someone in prison is working.)\n\nThe offender’s current employer displays a date in the end date field. Consider employer and address information unverified for community-based offenders. See <a><b><i>How do I manually Verify Employment and Address Information?</i></b></a>.\n\nIn the EMPLOYMENT INFORMATION screen click on the EYE to show the offenders’ wages and pay date information. It may also show the reason the offender left a job. This screen will display each employment record.\";i:1584373590088;s:1956:\"Access the OFFENDER pull down menu to display the CORE OFFENDER INFORMATION. Click on E-M and then Employment Information. See example below.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/WorkAssignments.png\" />\n\nThis screen displays a prisoner’s work history during their incarceration. Use this screen to see if someone in prison is working. If so, we can send an income withholding order to the prison to withhold from their earnings. Some inmates work outside of prison for a private company. They return to the prison when their work shift is completed. The name of the company the inmate is working for will be displayed by clicking on the \'\'EYE\'\'. An income withholding order can be sent to these employers in addition to the prison.\n\nThe EMPLOYMENT INFORMATION screen displays the inmate’s work assignments. If the end date field does not have a date in it, the person is currently working. A prisoner may be temporarily without a work assignment because they are being transferred to another facility, they are being disciplined or for other reasons. Therefore, you should not close an payor’s case under the assumption he or she will not have attachable income for the duration of their imprisonment if he or she does not have a current work assignment.\n\nOffenders entering prison are sent to Oakdale (IMCC) for classification. They do not have a work assignment while they are at Oakdale for classification. The majority of prisoners are then assigned to one of the other correctional facilities. A few prisoners do get assigned to serve their sentence at Oakdale and they may or may not have work assignments while they are there.\n\nICAR will load the prison as an employer during the AutoLocate process if they have a work assignment. When you add a prison as an employer for an offender, use the Inmate Accounts address for the prison in the employer database.\n\n[ninja_tables id=\"1063\"]\";i:1584373590320;s:769:\"Access the MOVEMENTS screen from the OFFENDER pull down menu (see example below) to see an offender’s supervision history. Death information is also displayed if the offender dies during their sentence.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/Movements.png\" />\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/Movement-access.png\" />\n\nAccess the TRANSFER screen from the OFFENDER pull down menu (see example below) to see a list of the prisoner\'\'s transfers.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/TransferScreen.png\" />\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/Transfers-access.png\" />\";i:1584373590624;s:523:\"Remember to change your password on a regular basis (recommended every 3 months). To change your password, access the <b>SYSTEM</b> drop-down menu, choose <b>Security</b>, then <b>Change Password</b>. See example below.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/Password-access.png\" />\n\nThen complete the fields on the Change Password screen to change your password.\n\n<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/03/PasswordScreen.png\" />\";i:1584373590896;s:648:\"The DOC maintains information on a large number of low risk offenders. The DOC is not required to maintain address and employment records for these offenders because the case manager’s caseload is approximately 1100 people.\n\n<b>How to Identify Low Risk Offenders:</b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Log onto ICON and pull up the record you want to view.</li>\n \t<li>Find the Levels section on the <b>OFFENDER INFORMATION</b> screen. This is the “Level of Supervision” field.</li>\n \t<li>If the LOS entry is “Low”, “Minimum” or “None”, <b>do not contact their case manager</b> for address and employment information.</li>\n</ul>\n\";i:1584373591192\";i:1584373591192;s:322:\"<b>Policy questions:</b>\nPlease e-mail the <a href=\"mailto:csrupolicy-location@dhs.state.ia.us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b>CSRU Policy - Location team</b></a>.\n\n<b>Technical issues:</b> ICAR Help Desk 1-515-281-5555. Please state you are having a problem with ICON.\n\n<b>Password problems:</b> Supervisor or MA2\";}"
