                     "meta_value": {
                        "__cdata": "a:4:{i:1586183954195;s:1110:\"<p>The Federal Benefit (FEDBEN) screen displays federal benefit information for payees, payors, alleged fathers and children on each ICAR case. You can access the screen by typing FEDBEN in any next screen field on ICAR.</p>\n<p>ICAR automatically updates the FEDBEN screen when we receive benefit information through the <a href=\"\"><b><i>Federal Case Registry</i></b></a> (FCR). Unfortunately, the FCR <b>does not</b> send benefit information for a case participant when any of the following is true:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The case participant has a family violence indicator (FVI).</li>\n<li>The case participant has an unverified SSN at the FCR level.</li>\n<li>The case participant is not registered on the FCR for some reason.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For these situations, <b>update the appropriate benefit fields on the FEDBEN screen when you verify the person\'s benefit status</b>.</p>\n<p>Enter a \"Y\" (Yes, benefits are being received) or an \"N\" (No, benefits are not being received) in the following fields on the FEDBEN screen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>SSIR</li>\n<li>SSID</li>\n<li>SSR</li>\n<li>SSD</li>\n<li>VA</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586183954969;s:104:\"<img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/FedbenScreen.gif\" />\";i:1586183955283;s:2137:\"<ul>\n<li><b>SSIR</b> - Supplemental Security Income Retirement (Aged Individual, age 65 or older)</li>\n<li><b>SSID</b> - Supplemental Security Income - Disability (Disabled Individual, any age)</li>\n<li><b>SSR</b> - Social Security Retirement (age 65 or older)</li>\n<li><b>SSD</b> - Social Security Disability (age 64 or younger)</li>\n<li><b>VA</b> - Veteran\'s Compensation and Pension</li>\n<li><b>RR</b> - Railroad Retirement</li>\n<li><b>Child field</b> - The screen will list <span style=\"color: red;\">all</span> children on the ICAR case.</li>\n<li><b>COMMENTS field</b> - Enter comments in this case specific field.</li>\n<li><b>Valid Entries</b>\n<p>Y = Yes, benefits are being received.<br />\nN = No, benefits are not being received.<br />\n- = Default entry.  We have not received benefit information.</p>\n<p>When the case participant who receives SSD benefits turns 65, SSA automatically switches those benefits to SSR, regardless of any existing disability. Therefore, you cannot enter a “Y” in both the ssr and ssd fields.</p>\n<p><b>Note:</b> There may be some case participants marked as receiving SSD who are between the ages of 62 and 64 who are actually receiving SSR. We are unable to differentiate between SSD and SSR records on the file SSA sends us. If you determine a case participant is receiving retirement benefits, it is best practice to make a note in the comment field on the FEDBEN screen. Once that person turns 65 years old, ICAR automatically enters a \"Y\" in the ssr field and places an \"N\" in the ssd field.</p>\n<p>A case participant who receives SSID may be over 65 years old if the participant was a \"Disabled Individual\" or \"Disabled Child\" prior to turning 65 years old. If a case participant was not disabled or stopped receiving SSID benefits before turning 65 years old, the participant may receive SSIR as an \"Aged Individual\". Therefore, you cannot enter \"Y\" at the same time in the ssir and ssid fields.</p>\n<p>A case participant may receive both Supplemental Security Income and Social Security Disability, so you can enter a \"Y\" in both the ssid and ssd fields.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586183955570;s:859:\"<ul>\n<li>The entries on the FEDBEN screen trigger updates to the ssd (y/n/r) and ssi (y/n/r) fields on the IWO2 screen for <a href=\"\"><b><i>hardship</i></b></a> purposes.</li>\n<li>The federal benefits field entries on the PAYEE2 and LOCATE screens and the fed ben field on the CHILD screen are based on the corresponding fields on the FEDBEN screen. A \"Y\" displays if any of the benefit fields on FEDBEN displays a \"Y\" for the person. You cannot change these entries on the PAYEE2, LOCATE and CHILD screens.</li>\n<li>ICAR automatically updates the LOCDB and the FEDBEN screens when we receive benefit information from the FCR. Review the LOCDB screens to verify the information is for the correct person. You can also find additional information on LOCDB regarding the case participant\'s benefit amount, address information, prison status, etc.</li>\n</ul>\";}"
