                     "meta_value": {
                        "__cdata": "a:6:{i:1586277833240;s:1919:\"<p>In May 2005, IDOT changed their vehicle registration process from VRHQ to VRT.  The official name of the system is Auto Registration and Titling System (ARTS).  IDOT and CSRU refer to the system as VRT. </p>\n<p>VRT contains information on any individual who has registered a vehicle in Iowa, or has a valid driver\'s license. Information available through VRT includes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name and address of the individual who registered the vehicle,</li>\n<li>The date of registration and renewal,</li>\n<li>A description of the vehicle, including type (i.e. auto, mobile home, truck, etc.),</li>\n<li>The status of the registration,</li>\n<li>Name, DOB, and address, including the mailing address of the individual,</li>\n<li>The issuance and expiration date of the driver\'s license,</li>\n<li>The driver\'s license number and customer number, and</li>\n<li>The status of the driver\'s license.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>IMPORTANT:</b> Dept. of Transportation information (VRT, and AUTOLOCIDOT) is subject to special confidentiality regulations. Always confirm VRT information with another source before verifying it as good.</p>\n<p>Access VRT through the Internet using the following url: <a href=\"https://arts.iowadot.gov/login.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><b>https://arts.iowadot.gov/login.aspx</b></a>.</p>\n<p>There are three ways to query the vehicle registration or driver\'s license database:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Through the owner’s name, SSN or drivers license number,</li>\n<li>Through the vehicle identification number or</li>\n<li>Through the license plate number</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Note:</b> The name, SSN or drivers license number query is the most common way to search VRT for location information.</p>\n<p>IDOT plans for this site mean that as time goes by, you will be able to see detailed information on all vehicles someone has owned or registered in the past. Meaning as the site ages so will the information. </p>\n\";i:1586269897079;s:2531:\"<p><b style=\"color: red;\">Reminder!</b> You must have authorization to access this site.</p>\n\n<p>Access to Driver record information is available to you through our new Driver Record system. The new system is the replacement for DLIC. This is web based and you can access it at <a href=\"https://arts.iowadot.gov/login.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><b>https://arts.iowadot.gov/login.aspx</b></a>. The userID is your first name.lastname. For example, John Doe’s user ID would be john.doe. Your initial password is Password123. You will be prompted to change it at first sign on.</p>\n<p>Navigate to the report by starting on the menu bar at the top of the page: Driver Reports > Customer History > Customer and DL/ID Information. When you click on \'Customer and DL/ID Information\' a Search screen appears.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/VrtCustomerSearch.png\" /></p>\n\n<p>You can search by an Identification number (SSN or DL) or by name. By default the Identification type is Drivers License. If you are searching by number, you should always click on the drop down arrow under Identification type and make it blank. If you are searching by name, be sure to uncheck the box \"Exact Match\" if you aren\'t entering the entire Last Name, First Name, etc. All the fields below the name fields are not used in searching for a Driver Record.</p>\n<p>The \"Search Results\" screen by default lists 10 records per page. You can sort the search results by clicking on the heading of the column.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/VrtSearchResults.gif\" /></p>\n\n<p>This is a combined customer database. Your results will include customers from both the Driver and Vehicle Registration transactions. If the Customer you are searching for has more than one entry, you need to look at the \"ConfidenceRating\" column on the far right. There are three possible confidence ratings:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><b>Authenticated:</b> Driver’s License issued since 4/13/07</li>\n<li><b>Unique:</b> Drivers License issued</li>\n<li><b>Other:</b> May be a duplicate vehicle record or a record we created because the person did not have an Iowa driver’s license (formerly “NDL” records).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You will want to select an Authenticated record first; if there isn’t an “Authenticated” you will then want to select the “Unique” record. You will only want to select the “Other” record if there isn’t anything else.</p>\";i:1586269901495;s:1405:\"<p>Once in the web site hover over the “Reports” option at the top of the screen. A drop down menu appears. Click on the “Plate Reports” option.</p>\n<p>A menu appears on the left side of your screen. Click on the “Plate History” option on the list.</p>\n<p>The “Plate History/Plate Search” screen appears. Enter the plate number in the “plate #” field and click SEARCH. If the plate number is valid, a detail screen appears. From this detail screen you can find out the following information:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vehicle Identification Number (VIN)</li>\n<li>Year of the vehicle (1999, 2000, 2001, etc.)</li>\n<li>Make of the vehicle (Jeep, Saturn, Hummer, Pontiac, etc.)</li>\n<li>Model of the vehicle (Cherokee, Ion, Grand Am, Silverado, etc.)</li>\n<li>Primary Owner (Name)</li>\n<li>Customer Address</li>\n<li>Updated by (who at DOT last worked on the registration)*</li>\n<li>Updated Date (date DOT last worked on the registration)**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>* If the update by field states “conversion” this is the date the information was moved from VRHQ to the web site. This means the record has not been updated since the conversion.</p>\n<p>** This date changes whenever the record is last updated.</p>\n<p>Make note of the “Primary Owner” name.</p>\n<p>You may link on the VIN in order to access more detailed information on the vehicle at the time of original registration.</p>\";i:1586269901838;s:1370:\"<p>Once in the web site hover over the “Reports” option at the top of the screen. A drop down menu appears. Click on the “Vehicle Reports” option.</p>\n<p>A menu appears on the left side of your screen. There are several options in this list, they are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vehicle Customer History</li>\n<li>Vehicle Ownership History</li>\n<li>Vehicle Plate History</li>\n<li>Vehicle Registration History</li>\n<li>Vehicle Registration Inquiry</li>\n<li>Vehicle Summary</li>\n<li>Vehicle Transaction History</li>\n</ul>\n<p>While the information on these screens is limited at this time, the details on these screens will increase overtime. As vehicles are bought and sold the information listed on these screen is updated to show all past and current owners. On most of the reports in this area the best information you can find on these reports is the last registration date for the vehicle. In order to access any information in this area you must know the Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) for each vehicle the person owns.</p>\n<p>The “Vehicle Registration Inquiry” can provide more detailed information. While most of the information on the report is as of date of purchase, the “customers” area provides:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The names of all registered owners,</li>\n<li>The dates of the registrations and</li>\n<li>The address of registration</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586269902142;s:1128:\"<p>Once in the web site hover over the “Drivers Reports” option at the top of the screen. A drop down menu appears. Click on the “Customer History” option.</p>\n<p>\"Customer History\" appears on the left side of your screen. Click on \"Customer and DL/ID information\".  The customer history brings up the customer search box. You may search this area by name, SSN, or driver’s license number. If you enter the customer’s social security number, do NOT put in the dashes (-).</p>\n<p>The search results provides the customer ID number, legal name, residency address, drivers license number, state, date of birth, and confidence rating.</p>\n<p>Click on the Customer ID number and it brings up the “Customer and DL/ID Information”.  If the driver license number is valid, a detail screen appears.  From this detail screen you can find out the following information:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name</li>\n<li>Address</li>\n<li>City/State</li>\n<li>Mailing Address</li>\n<li>DL/ID #</li>\n<li>Issue & Expiration Date</li>\n<li>Restrictions</li>\n<li>Date of Birth</li>\n<li>Customer #:</li>\n<li>ID, DL, and CDL Status</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586269902417;s:2764:\"<p>Once in the web site hover over the ‘Reports” option at the top of the screen. A drop down menu appears. Click on the “Customer reports” option.</p>\n<p>A menu appears on the left side of your screen. There are several options in this list, they are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Customer Ownership History</li>\n<li>Customer Registration History</li>\n<li>Customer Summary</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Think of this area as a funnel of information. The customer summary gives you an overview of the person, and does not provide information on vehicles. While the ownership and registration histories give you information on what vehicles a person owns and have registered to them. Keep in mind someone can have a vehicle registered in their name and NOT be the owner of the vehicle.</p>\n<p>You may search this area by name, SSN, driver’s license number, FEIN (if the vehicle is owned or registered to a business), or dealer number (if owned by a dealership). It is recommended that you search by both the SSN and the driver’s license number. Also, if you do not select an identification type, the search will occur under all options available giving you the greatest amount of feedback possible.</p>\n<p>When you run an ownership history each vehicle owned by that person displays. To see the details of the vehicle, click on the customer number for a listing. Another screen displays that tells you more about that vehicle the information includes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The VIN,</li>\n<li>A description of the vehicle,</li>\n<li>The primary owner,</li>\n<li>The registration address,</li>\n<li>Updated by (who at DOT last worked on the registration)*</li>\n<li>Updated Date (date DOT last worked on the registration)**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>* If the update by field states “conversion” this is the date the information was moved from VRHQ to the web site. This means the record has not been updated since the conversion.</p>\n<p>** This date changes whenever the record is last updated.</p>\n<p>When you run a registration history each vehicle registered to that person displays. To see the details of the vehicle, click on the customer number for a listing. Another screen displays that tells you more about that vehicle the information includes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The VIN,</li>\n<li>A description of the vehicle,</li>\n<li>The primary owner,</li>\n<li>The registration address,</li>\n<li>Updated by (who at DOT last worked on the registration)*</li>\n<li>Updated Date (date DOT last worked on the registration)**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>* If the update by field states “conversion” this is the date the information was moved from VRHQ to the web site. This means the record has not been updated since the conversion.</p>\n<p>** This date changes whenever the record is last updated.</p>\";}"
