                  {
                     "meta_key": {
                        "__cdata": "accordions_content_body"
                     },
                     "meta_value": {
                        "__cdata": "a:4:{i:1586455092710;s:1190:\"<p>The employer maintenance file contains information on thousands of employers.</p>\n<p>The information in this file includes, among other things:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Employer names</li>\n<li>Employer state IDs and Federal Employer Identification Numbers (FEINs)</li>\n<li>Physical/verification, IWO, and medical addresses</li>\n<li>Verification and medical companies and codes</li>\n<li>Phone and fax numbers</li>\n<li>E-mail addresses and company websites</li>\n<li>Whether the employer is out of business</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ICAR Maintenance staff maintain the employer maintenance file - adding new employers, removing old ones, and updating information.</p>\n<p>Workers help maintain the file by contacting the ICAR Maintenance team when company information changes or a company goes out of business, and by adding new employers to EMPVER and CPEMPVER screens. ICAR Maintenance staff use this information when adding and updating records.</p>\n<p>ICAR and workers use information in the employer maintenance file for a variety of reasons, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Verifying employment</li>\n<li>Establishing IWOs</li>\n<li>Verifying health insurance</li>\n<li>Contacting companies</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586455093008;s:497:\"<p>You can access the employer maintenance file one of two ways:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>View the employer maintenance file from the View Employer Maintenance screens (VEMPLOY & VEMPLOY2). See Employer Maintenance Screen for details.</li>\n<li>Search limited file data and link EMPVER screens to employers in the file from the Employer Name Address Search screen. Access this screen by pressing F6 from an EMPVER or CPEMPVER screen. See the Guide to Adding and Formatting Employers for details.</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586455093251;s:861:\"<p>Only the ICAR Maintenance team can update the employer maintenance file. This ensures the highest quality of information, and prevents duplicate records for the same employer.</p>\n<p>Field staff can add employer records to EMPVER and CPEMPVER screens. These records may be \"linked\" - connected to and displaying information from the employer maintenance file - or \"unlinked\" - not connected.</p>\n<p>Whenever you verify an employer as a good employer (emp verified = Y on an EMPVER or CPEMPVER screen), you must either:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Link the employer to the employer maintenance file;</li>\n<br />\n<p>OR</p>\n<li>Verify the employer information; and</li>\n<li>Format the employer name and address according to ICAR and postal standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See the <a href=\"\"><b><i>Guide to Adding and Updating Employers</i></b></a> for more information.</p>\";i:1586455093531;s:988:\"<p>If you find missing, changed, or inaccurate information on the employer maintenance file, send an e-mail to the <a href=\"\"><b><i>ICAR Maintenance Mailbox</i></b></a>. The ICAR Maintenance team will review the information and make appropriate changes.</p>\n<p>Contact Roger Fee if you find out the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The employer is out of business.</li>\n<li>The employer moved.</li>\n<li>The employer changed contact information such as:\n<ul>\n<li>Phone and fax numbers</li>\n<li>Contact names</li>\n<li>Preferred method of contact</li>\n<li>E-mail address</li>\n<li>Website</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>The employer provided a different IWO or medical address.</li>\n<li>The employer uses an employment verification service.</li>\n<li>The employer is listed under a legal name (such as AG Enterprise’s), but uses a different common name (such as Carl’s Place).</li>\n<li>If you had trouble finding an employer because the name was not formatted to current standards.</li>\n</ul>\";}"
                     }
