                  {
                     "meta_key": {
                        "__cdata": "accordions_content_body"
                     },
                     "meta_value": {
                        "__cdata": "a:4:{i:1586455916667;s:10752:\"<p><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/VemployScreen.gif\" /></p>\n<p>A new function key was added to EMPVER, CPEMPVER and VEMPLOY. The new key is F14. The F14 key can be used on EMPVER/CPEMPVER screens when the employer has an ICAR EMPLOYER ID. The F14 key will take you to the VEMPLOY screens for the employer you are currently viewing.  On the VEMPLOY screens, you can view all data stored on ICAR for that employer. Once you have viewed all the data for an employer on the VEMPLOY screen you can return to the EMPVER/CPEMPVER screen by using the F14 key.</p>\n<p>The VEMPLOY screens contain data separated into three main sections. The first section contains the data for the location of employment, the second section contains the IWO data and the third section, which you view by using F11 on VEMPLOY contains the medical data. In comments you will see additional information and numbers for contacting employers. A comment of V = phone number, means this is a separate number to be used for employment verifications.</p>\n\n<p><b>VEMPLOY field descriptions</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>employer id:</b> This field displays a unique number assigned to each employer. ICAR assigns this number to the employer when ICER staff adds the employer to the <a href=\"\"><b><i>Employer Maintenance File</i></b></a>.</li>\n<li><b>last upd:</b> This field displays the last date someone updated the employer information.</li>\n<li><b>by:</b> This field displays the Worker ID or Program ID which last updated the employer listing. Central Office and the ICAR team use this field for tracking and troubleshooting purposes.</li>\n<li><b>federal id:</b> This field displays one of three identifiers for the employer. Valid entries for the federal id field in order of greatest frequency:\n<ul>\n<li>Federal Employee Identification Number (FEIN)</li>\n<li>Blank</li>\n<li>Social Security Identification Number</li>\n<li>State assigned Tax Identification Number</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>verify svc:</b> This field displays a two-digit number the policy unit assigns to the employment verification service. Valid entries for this field are:\n<ul>\n<li>Blank: The employer does not use an employment verification service</li>\n<li>01: Indicates <a href=\"\"><b><i>TALX/The Work Number (TWN)</i></b></a></li>\n</ul>\nAs the employment verification market grows, Central Office will create additional codes for this field.</li>\n<li><b>code:</b> This field displays the verification number the service company (listed in the verify svc field) assigns to the employer. Use this employer-specific code when contacting the company that processes employment verifications.</li>\n<li><b>employer name:</b> This field displays the trade name of the employer.</li>\n<li><b>out of business:</b>  See <a href=\"\"><b><i>(Y/U)</i></b></a> below.</li>\n<li><b>address line 1:</b> This field displays the location of employment.<br />\nIf the street address does not fit on one line, the address is separated into two parts.\n<ul>\n<li>address line 1 displays the apartment, suite, or unit number.</li>\n<li>address line 2 displays the street address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>(y/u):</b> This field indicates if the employer is out of business and, if so, when. Valid entries in the first character of this field are:\n<ul>\n<li>Y: The employer has gone out of business</li>\n<li>U: Mail to the employer at this address has been returned as undeliverable</li>\n<li>Blank: The employer is still in business</li>\n</ul>\nThe rest of the field displays the date the employer went out of business or the date mail was returned undeliverable.</li>\n<li><b>address line 2:</b> This field displays the location of employment.<br />\nIf the street address does not fit on one line, the address is separated into two parts.\n<ul>\n<li>address line 1 displays the apartment, suite, or unit number.</li>\n<li>address line 2 displays the street address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>mail to loc:</b> This field is not currently used. The valid entry is:\n<ul>\n<li>Y: The employer prefers the Unit send verification of employment to the location of employment and not to the IWO address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>city/state/zip:</b> This field displays the city, state, and ZIP code for location of employment.</li>\n<li><b>contact name:</b> This field displays the contact person name at the location of employment.</li>\n<li><b>phone:</b> This field displays the phone number provided by the employer or found through research.</li>\n<li><b>ext:</b> This field displays the phone extension provided by the employer or found through research.</li>\n<li><b>email:</b> This field displays the e-mail address provided by the employer.</li>\n<li><b>fax:</b> This field displays the fax number provided by the employer.</li>\n<li><b>method of contact:</b> This field indicates how employer wishes to be contacted. Valid entries are as follows:\n<ul>\n<li>P: Prefers to be contacted by telephone.</li>\n<li>F: Prefers to be contacted by fax.</li>\n<li>E: Prefers to be contacted by e-mail.</li>\n<li>W: Prefers to be contacted through the \"Contact Us\" option on their company’s Web page (see <a href=\"\"><b><i>VEMPLOY2</i></b></a>).</li>\n<li>M: Prefers to be contacted by mail.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>update all empl:</b> This field indicates if the following information will be copied to this company’s other locations (those with the same base (9-digit) FEIN):\n<ul>\n<li>verify svc & code</li>\n<li>Main location’s contact name, email and phone, ext, and fax numbers</li>\n<li>Entries in all but the first section of the electronic field</li>\n<br />ICER staff use this field when updating employer information. The valid entry is: \n<li>Y: ICER staff are waiting for the system to copy information to other locations’ records.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<p><b>iwo emp name:</b> This field displays the legal, trade or corporate name for the company.</li>\n<li><b>electronic:</b> These fields indicate whether this employer participates in electronic forms and communications.\n<br />\nThe first field indicates whether this employer participates in receiving electronic forms through Military IWO\'s. Valid entries are as follows:\n<ul>\n<li><b>D</b> - The employer participates through the Department of Finance and Accounting Service (DFAS).</li>\n<li><b>N</b> - The employer does not participate.</li>\n<li><b>Blank</b> - The employer does not participate.</li>\n<br />\nThe second field indicates whether this employer participates in Electronic Funds Transfer.  Valid entries are as follows:  \n<li><b>F</b> - The employer submits payments through electronic funds transfer (EFT).</li>\n<li><b>Z</b> - The employer is not interested in submitting payments through EFT.</li>\n<li><b>Blank</b> - The employer <span style=\"color: red;\">does not participate</span>.</li>\n<br />\nThe third and fourth fields indicate whether this employer is registered with the employer’s website (iowachildsupport.gov). Valid entries are as follows: \n<li><b>H</b> - The employer is registered to submit new hire information through the website.</li>\n<li><b>R</b> - The employer is registered, but does not report new hires or make payments through the website.</li>\n<li><b>W</b> - The employer is registered to submit payments through the site.</li>\n<li><b>X</b> - The employer is not interested in registering with the website.</li>\n<li><b>Blank</b> - The employer does not participate.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>forms:</b> These fields indicate whether this employer participates in receiving electronic forms through the employer’s website (iowachildsupport.gov).<br />\nThe first field indicates whether the employer receives income withholding forms through the website. Income withholding forms are all immediate, mandatory, amended and terminated regular and lump-sum income withholding notices as well as payment inquiries that generate from the “<a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/IWO/Contents/Flowcharts/IWO%20Monitor%20For%20Flow%20Chart.pdf\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/pdf.png\"> <b>Monitor For</b></a>” program. Valid entries are as follows:\n<ul>\n<li><b>Y</b> - The employer is receiving IWO forms through the website.</li>\n<li><b>N</b> - The employer no longer receives IWO forms through the website.</li>\n<li><b>Blank</b> - The employer does not receive IWO forms through the website.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>iwo addr line 1:</b> This field displays the address to which IWOs should be sent. If the address does not fit on one line, the address is separated into two parts:\n<ul>\n<li>iwo addr line 1 displays the <i>In care of (%)</i> department or accounting firm; or displays the apartment, suite, or unit number.</li>\n<li>iwo addr line 2 displays the street address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>iwo addr line 2:</b> This field displays the address to which IWOs should be sent. If the address does not fit on one line, the address is separated into two parts:\n<ul>\n<li>iwo addr line 1 displays the <i>In care of (%)</i> department or accounting firm or displays the apartment, suite, or unit number.</li>\n<li>iwo addr line 2 displays the street address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>update all iwoaddr:</b> This field indicates if the following IWO information will be copied to this company’s other locations (those with the same base (9-digit) FEIN):\n<ul>\n<li>iwo emp name</li>\n<li>iwo addr line 1 & 2, city/state/zip</li>\n<li>contact name, email and phone, ext, and fax numbers</li>\n<br />\nICER staff use this field when updating employer information. The valid entry is: \n<li>Y: ICER staff are waiting for the system to copy information to other locations’ records.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>income provider:</b> This field is not currently used.\n<br />This field indicates if the company is an income provider or an employer. Valid entries are:\n<ul>\n<li>Blank: The company is an employer.</li>\n<li>Y: The company is an income provider (e.g. Workman’s Comp or SSA).</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>city/state/zip:</b> This field displays the City, State, and Zip code for location of payroll.</li>\n<li><b>contact name:</b> This field displays the contact person name at the location of payroll.</li>\n<li><b>phone:</b> This field displays the phone number to use when verifying IWO data.</li>\n<li><b>ext:</b> This field displays the phone extension to use when verifying IWO data.</li>\n<li><b>email:</b> This field displays the e-mail address to use when verifying IWO data.</li>\n<li><b>fax:</b> This field displays the fax number to use when verifying IWO data.</li>\n<li><b>comments:</b> This field displays text related to the fields on this screen.</li>\";i:1586455916855;s:6770:\"<p><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/VemployScreen.gif\" /></p>\n\n<h4>VEMPLOY2 field descriptions</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li><b>employer id:</b> This field displays a unique number assigned to each employer. ICAR assigns this number to the employer when ICER staff adds the employer to the <a href=\"\"><b><i>Employer Maintenance File</i></b></a>.</li>\n<li><b>federal id:</b> This field displays an employer identifier assigned by state or Federal agencies. Valid entries for the federal id field in order of greatest frequency and priority: \n<ul>\n<li>Federal Employee Identification Number (FEIN)</li>\n<li>Social Security Identification Number</li>\n<li>State assigned Tax Identification Number</li>\n<li>Blank</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>medical svc:</b> This field displays a two-digit number the policy unit assigns to the medical service. This field is not currently used.</li>\n<li><b>code:</b> This field displays the verification number the service company listed in the medical svc field assigns to the employer. Use this employer-specific code when contacting the company that processes medical forms. This field is not currently used.</li>\n<li><b>employer name:</b> This field displays the employer\'s trade name.</li>\n<li><b>nmsn instr:</b> This field indicates if the unit sends instructions with the National Medical Support Notice. Valid entries for this field are:\n<ul>\n<li>Y: Employer receives instructions with the notice.</li>\n<li>N: Employer requested we no longer send instructions with the notice.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>med emp name:</b> This field displays the name of the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>bypass medical:</b> This field indicates if the company provides health insurance for its employees’ dependents. Valid entries are as follows:\n<ul>\n<li>Blank: Default.</li>\n<li>Y: The employer never provides health insurance for its employees\' dependents.</li>\n</ul>\nWhen this field displays a Y, Central Office bypasses the employer for MEDSUM processing.</li>\n<li><b>med addr line 1:</b> This field displays the address of the company that processes medical forms for the employer. \nIf the address does not fit on one line, the address is separated into two parts:\n<ul>\n<li>med addr line 1 displays the apartment, suite, or unit number.</li>\n<li>med addr line 2 displays the street address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>military:</b> This field indicates if the company is a branch of the United States Armed Services. Valid entries are:\n<ul>\n<li>Y: The company is a branch of the US Armed Services.</li>\n<li>Blank: The company is not a branch of the US Armed Services.</li>\n</ul>\nA Y in this field prevents the generation of medical support enforcement forms. When medical support enforcement is appropriate, a calendar flag generates instructing the worker to contact the obligee to apply for health insurance at the nearest Defense Enrollment Eligibility Reporting System (DEERS) facility.</li>\n<li><b>med addr line 2:</b> This field displays the address of the company that processes medical forms for the employer. \nIf the address does not fit on one line, the address is separated into two parts:\n<ul>\n<li>med addr line 1 displays the apartment, suite, or unit number.</li>\n<li>med addr line 2 displays the street address.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>city/state/zip:</b> This field displays the city, state and ZIP code of the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>contact name:</b> This field displays the contact person for the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>phone:</b> This field displays the phone number of the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>ext:</b> This field displays the phone extension number of the contact person for the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>email:</b> This field displays the e-mail address of the contact person for the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>fax:</b> This field displays the fax number for the company that processes medical forms for the employer.</li>\n<li><b>website:</b> This field displays the Internet address for the company. The company web site may contain additional contact resource information, such as mailing addresses, telephone numbers, or email accounts.</li>\n<li><b>update all medaddr:</b> This field indicates if the following medical information will be copied to this company’s other locations (those with the same base (9-digit) FEIN):\n<ul>\n<li>med emp name</li>\n<li>med addr line 1 & 2, city/state/zip</li>\n<li>contact name, email, and phone, ext, and fax numbers</li>\nICER staff use this field when updating employer information. The valid entry is: \n<li>Y: ICER staff are waiting for the system to copy information to other locations’ records.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>bypass employer:</b> This field indicates if various ICAR processes bypass this employer. Valid entries for this field are:\n<ul>\n<li>N: The employer is not bypassed</li>\n<li>Y: The employer is bypassed</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>sdu notice sent:</b> This field indicates if the Unit sent information regarding distribution to the employer. The State Disbursement Unit tracks this field. Valid entries for this field are:\n<ul>\n<li>Y: Information has been mailed</li>\n<li>N: Information has not been mailed</li>\n<li>O: The employer is bypassed for mailing (used for multiple store chains)</li>\n<li>Blank: No action has been taken</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>outreach:</b> This field indicates if the Unit sent outreach materials to the employer and when.  Valid entries for the first character are:\n<ul>\n<li>Y: Resource materials were sent</li>\n<li>O: The employer was omitted from the list of those to receive resource materials</li>\n<li>N: Resource materials have not been sent at this time</li>\nThe rest of the field displays the date the Unit extracted addresses for the mailing.\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>date:</b> indicates the date the address file was extracted to distribute outreach materials to the employer.</li>\n<li><b>multi st emp rep to:</b> This field displays the state to which a multi-state employer reports new hires. Valid entries are:\n<ul>\n<li>Blank: The employer:\n<ul>\n<li>Has employees only in Iowa, or</li>\n<li>The employer has employees in multiple states and reports new hires to the states in which the employees work</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>A state abbreviation: The employer has employees in more than one state and reports all new hire information to the indicated state.</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>comments:</b> This field displays text related to the fields on this screen.</li>\n</ul>\";i:1586455917059;s:3943:\"<p>The <b>VEMPLOY</b> and <b>VEMPLOY2</b> screens use the same function keys.</p>\n<p>ICAR displays the following at the bottom of the VEMPLOY and VEMPLOY2 screens:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>F2=ADD</li>\n<li>F3=MODIFY</li>\n<li>F4=DELETE</li>\n<li>F5=INQUIRE</li>\n<li>F6=DELETE IWO</li>\n<li>F7=BACKWARD</li>\n<li>F8=FORWARD</li>\n<li>F9=REFRESH</li>\n<li>F10=INQUIRE IWO</li>\n<li>F11=EMPLOY2</li>\n</ul>\n<p>However, you can only use the following function keys on this screen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>F5 (Inquire)</li>\n<li>F8 (Forward)</li>\n<li>F11 (Employ2)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<p><b>F5 (Inquire)</b></p>\n<p>You can search for employers on the VEMPLOY and VEMPLOY2 screens by one of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ICAR Employer ID</li>\n<li>First nine digits of the Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN)</li>\n<li>Complete (12-digit) FEIN</li>\n<li>Employer Name</li>\n\n<p><b>Searching by Employer ID</b></p>\n<p>To search for an employer by the ICAR employer ID, type the complete employer ID in the employer id field and press F5.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If the employer ID matches an employer in the file, ICAR displays the employer information.</li>\n<li>If the employer ID does not match an employer in the file, ICAR displays the message: EMPLOYER NOT FOUND USING STATE ID.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Searching by 9-Digit FEIN</b></p>\n<p>To search for an employer by the first 9 digits of the FEIN, type the first 9 digits of the FEIN in the federal id field and press F5.</p>\n<p>ICAR displays the EMPLOYER NAME ADDRESS SEARCH screen.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ICAR displays employers in order of their FEIN, beginning with the FEIN you entered.</li>\n<li>If the FEIN you entered does not match any employer on the file, ICAR displays the employer with the next highest FEIN.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use the F7 (back) and F8 (forward) keys to page through the employers.</p>\n<p>To select an employer record, tab to the SEL field to the left of the employer. Enter an “S” or an “X” and press ENTER.  ICAR displays that employer’s information.</p>\n<p><b>Searching by Complete FEIN</b></p>\n<p>To search for an employer by a complete FEIN, type the FEIN in the federal id field and press F5.</p>\n<p>If the FEIN matches an employer in the file, ICAR displays the employer information.</p>\n<p>If the FEIN does not match an employer in the file, ICAR displays the message: EMPLOYER NOT FOUND USING FIN NUMBER.</p>\n<p><b>Searching by Employer Name</b></p>\n<p>To search for an employer by employer name, enter all or part of the employer name in the employer name field.</p>\n<p>ICAR displays the EMPLOYER NAME ADDRESS SEARCH screen.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ICAR displays employers in alphabetical order, beginning with the name you entered.</li>\n<li>When more than one employer record has the same name (for example, a chain restaurant), ICAR further sorts the employer alphabetically by city.</li>\n<li>If the name you entered does not match any employer on the file, ICAR displays the next employer.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use the F7 (back) and F8 (forward) keys to page through the employers.</p>\n<p>To select an employer record, tab to the SEL field to the left of the employer. Enter an “S” or an “X” and press ENTER. ICAR displays that employer’s information.</p>\n</ul>\n<p><b>F8 (Forward)</b></p>\n<p>If the ICAR Maintenance team changed information for this employer, press the F8 key to see the old information.</p>\n<p><b>F11 (VEMPLOY or VEMPLOY2)</b></p>\n<p>Use F11 to toggle between the VEMPLOY and VEMPLOY2 screen for an employer.</p>\n<p>If you are on the VEMPLOY screen, press F11 to view the VEMPLOY2 screen.</p>\n<p>If you are on the VEMPLOY2 screen, press F11 to view the VEMPLOY screen.</p>\n<p><b>Note:</b> You cannot use the F11 key until you inquire on an employer (F5).</p>\n<p>To view the other screen when you are not currently viewing an employer record, type “VEMPLOY” or “VEMPLOY2” in the next screen field and press ENTER.</p>\";i:1586526724914;s:6956:\"<p>National employment verification services, such as VerifyAdvantage, or TALX The Work Number (TWN), contract with employers to answer incoming employment verification requests.</p>\n<p>Treat returned information from employment verification service providers the same as you would a completed EMPVER letter.</p>\n\n<p><b>How Employment Verification Services Work</b></p>\n<p>When an employer contracts with an employment verification service, it provides detailed salary and employment information about its employees.</p>\n<p>When the employer receives an employment verification request, it redirects the request to the service. The service usually charges the requestor a fee when providing the information. However, because employers cannot charge child support recovery units for employment verification, the service provides cost-free employment verification for child support recovery units.</p>\n<p>Warning: Narrate your actions if you request verification from an employment verification service. Create a calendar flag to follow-up on the request. </p>\n\n<p><b>Employment Verification from the U. S. Postal Service (USPS)</b></p>\n<p>The USPS no longer replies to requests for employment verification. This service is now provided by TALX - The Work Number (TWN).</p>\n<p>For more information see <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Location/Contents/NonAutoLocate/EmpVerifyServiceProviders/EmployeeInformationRequest.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/pdf.png\"> <b>Requests for USPS Employee Information</b></a> or  <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Location/Contents/NonAutoLocate/EmpVerifyServiceProviders/IM-08-06%20Employment%20Verification%20from%20USPS.doc\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/word.png\"> <b>Information Memorandum IM-08-06</b></a>. </p>\n\n<p><b>How to Request Verification Through VerifyAdvantage</b></p>\n<p>You can access VerifyAdvantage at the following web address: <a href=\"https://www.verifyadvantage.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><b>https://www.verifyadvantage.com</b></a>. Passwords are case sensitive and must include a capital and lower case letter, a special character, a number and must be 8 characters.</p>\n<p><b>Warning:</b> Check with your Supervisor before registering to determine if your office will have one e-mail address and password for the entire office or if more than one person will be allowed to register.</p>\n<p>To register and log-in, you will need the following information:</p> \n<ul>\n<li>On the VerifyAdvantage home page click the <b>Create Account</b> link under the Government Requestor section.</li>\n<li>On the Government Requestor Account Setup page complete the required fields and click, <b>Create Account</b>.</li>\n<p><b>Note:</b> Make sure to enter your government office work email address, work fax/phone (include area code) and work mailing address.</p>\n<li>Complete the required fields on the Government Requestor Account Setup page and press the OK button.</li>\n<li>You will receive an email containing instructions to complete the setup process.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>VerifyAdvantage sends responses within 24 hours. If you do not receive your verification request, please call VerifyAdvantage at 1-866-894-7687.</p>\n\n<p><b>How to Request Verification Through TALX - The Work Number (TWN)</b></p>\n<p>TALX - The Work Number (TWN) is an employment verification service. Your office\'s designated staff member(s) can request employment verification through the <a href=\"http://www.theworknumber.com/SocialServices/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><b>website</b></a>.</p>\n<p>Supervisors will contact the regional MA2s when workers need to be added or removed from the TWN website. The Regional MA2s will add users, deactivate users, and assist users with password issues.</p>\n<p>When you are initially added as a user to the website, you will receive an automated email with a subject of \"Account Password - The Work Number.\" That email will explain how to establish your own password.</p>\n<p>To log-in and request verification, you will need the following information:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Your user name and password.</b></li>\n<li><b>The employee\'s Social Security Number.</b><br />\nTWN matches employment records using SSNs. If you do not have the employee\'s SSN, you cannot request verification.</li>\n<li><b>The employer\'s TWN company code.</b><br />\nTWN assigns each employer a unique company code. To find a code, you can:\n<ul>\n<li>Check the TWN website;</li>\n<li>Check the VEMPLOY screen on ICAR (not all TWN employers are listed on ICAR). If the TWN company code is on the VEMPLOY screen, it will look like the following.</li>\n<p>VERIFY SVC: 01 TALX CODE: 99999</p>\n</ul></li>\n<li><b>Permissible Purpose</b><br />\nTWN requires you to select a permissible purpose. The options provided on the TWN website for permissible purpose correspond with the applicable language in the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA). See <a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Location/Contents/NonAutoLocate/EmpVerifyServiceProviders/Permissible%20Purpose%20Options%20in%20TALX-TWN.docx\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/word.png\"> <b>Permissible Purpose Options in TALX-TWN</b></a> for screen prints and directions for selecting a permissible purpose.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Only use the Chrome browser when accessing the TWN site.  Users have experienced problems when other browsers are used.</p>\n<p>TWN verification will be available for viewing and printing on line after 5 business days. Orders will only be available to view one time. If you open an order and then close it, the order will immediately disappear. You will not be able to access it again. Once you open the order, it must be processed immediately. If the order is left unopened, it will stay available for up to 30 days in the \"My orders\" tab.</p>\n<p>For policy questions on Verify Advantage or TWN please e-mail the <a href=\"mailto:CSRUPolicy-Location@dhs.state.ia.us\" target=\"_blank\"><b>CSRU Policy - Location team</b></a></p>\n\n<p><b>Restricted Employment Verification Service Providers</b></p>\n<p>CSRU cannot use the employment verification service providers listed below. Most either had problems with their terms and conditions or had FCRA language that was outdated or inaccurate.</p>\n<p><b>DO NOT USE:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>CCC Verify</li>\n<li>DriverFacts</li>\n<li>Empcheck.com (EmployCheck)</li>\n<li>Employers Unity</li>\n<li>EVAdvantage</li>\n<li>i2Verify</li>\n<li>Inverify (Requests may be sent over by fax to obtain employment verifications. Casey\'s employers currently use Inverify. Inverify fax #: 720-358-2700.)</li>\n<li>Tenstreet</li>\n<li>Thomas & Company</li>\n<li>uConfirm</li>\n<li>Vault Verify</li>\n<li>Verifyfast</li>\n<li>VerifyToday</li>\n<li>WAGEverify</li>\n</ul>\";}"
