                        "__cdata": "a:5:{i:1587396515302;s:240:\"<p><a href=\"file://hoovr3s2/CSRU.772/CS_TRAIN/Caretaker_Training\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/folder.png\"> <b>July 2007 Caretaker Training ppt. Presentation</b></a></p>\";i:1587396515610;s:2769:\"<p><a href=\"file://hoovr3s2/CSRU.772/CSRUPROC/Directives/2004\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/folder.png\"> <b>04-14 - Displaying Obligation on Caretaker Cases</b></a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"file://hoovr3s2/CSRU.772/CSRUPROC/Directives/2007\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/folder.png\"> <b>07-07 - New CHILD HISTORY Screens & Changes to ICAR Caretaker Fields</b></a></p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h4>PD 08-04 Announcement</h4>\n<p>-----Original Message-----<br />\nFrom: Strain, Kirk<br />\nSent: Monday, June 30, 2008 1:49 PM<br />\nTo: CSRU Policy Information<br />\nSubject: Procedural Directive #PD 08-04 - Re-direction of support in caretaker cases</p>\n<p>Procedural Directive 08-04 - Re-direction of support in caretaker cases is now available on the server -</p>\n<p><a href=\"file://hoovr3s2/csru.772/CSRUPROC/Directives\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/folder.png\"> <b>Hoovr3s2csru.772CSRUPROCDirectives</b></a> It is located in the 2008 folder.</p>\n<p>Iowa Code Chapter 252A.13 requires the assignment of support by operation of law when a caretaker applies for and receives IV-A assistance for the child(ren) in their care. While the statute provides a clear indication that the State may not retain more support than is necessary for the reimbursement of that assistance, the statute is silent as to whom receives any overage associated with these cases.</p>\n<p>To clarify this situation Policy staff and Unit Attorneys have developed a process to re-direct the support on caretaker cases from the current payee for the impacted order to the caretaker. This PD clarifies the ownership of any overage that may be associated with the caretaker case.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding this PD, please contact any member of the Distribution team through normal channels.</p>\n<p>Hard copies of the signed document will be distributed accordingly. Original will be filed in BOC library.</p>\n<p>Thank you.</p>\n<p>Kirk</p>\n<p>Kirk Strain<br />\nBureau of Collections<br />\n400 SW 8th St. Ste. M<br />\nDes Moines, IA 50300-4691</p>\n<p>515-242-3238 phone<br />\n515-281-8854 fax</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<p><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Caretaker/Contents/InfoSentToStaff/pd0803.doc\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/word.png\"> <b>PD 08-03</b></a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Caretaker/Contents/InfoSentToStaff/pd0801.doc\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/word.png\"> <b>PD 08-01</b></a></p>\";i:1587396515867;s:321:\"<p><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Caretaker/Contents/Questions%20-%20Field%20Staff%20Caretaker%20Training%207-9-07(Revised).doc\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/word.png\"> <b>Caretaker Training for Field Workers Q & A 7-9-07</b></a></p>\n\";i:1587396516093;s:4853:\"<h4>New forms for Caretaker Assignments</h4>\n<p><b>(includes PD 08-04)</b></p>\n<p>-----Original Message-----<br />\nFrom: Pollard, Terri<br />\nSent: Friday, June 27, 2008 2:04 PM<br />\nTo: CSRU Policy Information<br />\nSubject: New forms for Caretaker Assignments</p>\n<p>Please share this note with all appropriate staff.</p>\n<p>In our continuing effort to enhance and clarify the caretaker process, four new forms were developed to re-direct support to caretakers when the caretaker receives assistance (FIP) for the child(ren) in their care.</p>\n<p>Starting immediately, when you activate an 11 account type case where the payee is a caretaker and the court order is from Iowa, generate a motion and order to re-direct the support to the caretaker. There are two sets of forms to use for this re-direction process:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Forms 470-4543 (motion) and 470-4544 (order) when a single child is covered by the order and is now with a caretaker.</li>\n<li>Forms 470-4545 (motion) and 470-4546 (order) when multiple children are covered by the order and are now with a caretaker.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note: On the multiple child forms you can indicate whether all of the children are with the caretaker or some of the children are with the caretaker.</p>\n<p>You can generate the forms using a new field CT M/O and ATTY on the PAYEE2 screen.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>To generate forms 470-4543 and 470-4544, enter S and the worker ID for the attorney who will sign the motion in the field. Once you modify the screen, ICAR presents the forms to you in order.</li>\n<li>To generate forms 470-4545 and 470-4546, enter M and the worker ID for the attorney who will sign the motion in the field. Once you modify the screen, ICAR presents the forms to you in order.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The PD attached to this e-mail provides additional information in the use of these forms.</p>\n<p>Thanks to attorneys Joaquin Jones, Jade Haverman, Michael Parker, and SRS Jim Cruchelow for their assistance in the development of these forms. If you have any questions regarding these forms, please contact any member of the Distribution Team through normal channels.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://intra/csruhandbooks/HANDBOOKS/Caretaker/Contents/InfoSentToStaff/PD%2008-04%20Caretaker%20Re-directions.doc\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://stcsruportalcli.blob.core.windows.net/csruportalwpcontent/2020/04/word.png\"> <b>PD 08-04 Caretaker Re-directions</b></a></p>\n<p>Terri Pollard<br />\nCentral Office<br />\n515-242-6096</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h4>Entering Court Order Numbers</h4>\n<p>-----Original Message-----<br />\nFrom: Granberg, Siri<br />\nSent: Wednesday, July 11, 2007 9:26 AM<br />\nTo: CSRU Policy Information<br />\nSubject: Entering Court Order Numbers<br />\nImportance: High</p>\n<p>Please share with all appropriate staff.</p>\n<p>As we implement the caretaker project, please remember to enter court order numbers correctly on the COURTORD screen.</p>\n<p>When entering court order numbers into the ICIS C.O. NUMBER field on the COURTORD screen, remember to enter 4 letters and 6 numbers. If the document you have doesn\'t have 4 letters and 6 numbers, please:<br />\nCheck the ICIS system for the full court order number.<br />\nReview the Case Set Appendix for a list of letter combinations for the county of filing.<br />\nEnter zeros in front of the numbers you do have until you reach 6 digits.</p>\n<p>For example, the document you have shows CD1234 as the court order number for Jackson County. The Case Set Up Appendix shows the letter combination for Jackson County is CVCD, and you know you need 6 numbers. Enter CVCD001234 in the ICIS C.O. NUMBER field.</p>\n<p>Entering all 4 characters and all 6 numbers in the ICIS C.O. NUMBER field helps ICAR match with the ICIS system. In the past, duplicate cases loaded to ICAR. When an ICIS case comes through the State Case Registry, a program compares the court order number from ICIS system to ICAR to see if the case exists. When the court order numbers don\'t match exactly, ICAR thinks it is a new number, and builds a new case.</p>\n<p>When you work a case, we recommend that you review the court order number to see if the format is right; if not, please update the screen. Remember to update the COURT ORDER NUMBER field for all Iowa orders when you see a different format on the ICIS system for the same court docket number. This allows the ICIS C.O. NUMBER field and the COURT ORDER NUMBER field to match. If you are filing an out-of-state order for enforcement, keep the other state\'s court docket number in the COURT ORDER NUMBER field and enter the Iowa ICIS number in the ICIS C.O. NUMBER field and the Iowa county FIPS in the REG/FILE COUNTY FIPS field.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding this case set up information, please contact Siri Granberg.</p>\n<p>Siri Granberg<br />\n515-281-4290</p>\";i:1587396516344;s:1486:\"<p><b>What do you do when you have multiple cases for the same child and payor and the order is from another state? How do you know how many Transmittal #1’s to complete and send to the other state? How do you know what the other state requires?</b></p>\n<p><b>BEST PRACTICE TIPS</b></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Contact the other state’s Central Registry to find out this information. (Central Registry contact information can be obtained through the <a href=\"https://extranet.acf.hhs.gov/irg/welcome.html\" target=\"_blank\"><b>IRG</b></a> (Intergovernmental Referral Guide). Explain your case scenario(s) and ask the other state to provide you with an explanation of what you are required to send to obtain the results you are needing, (i.e., child support redirected from the mom vs. dad case to the caretaker, etc.).</li>\n<br />\n<p><b>Note:</b> It is important to remember that states differ in their laws as to what they can and cannot do.</p>\n<li>Refer to the IRG (Intergovernmental Referral Guide).  Information on how to <a href=\"https://dhsquickproxy.dhs.state.ia.us/fsf/userCertification.html\" target=\"_blank\"><b>access and use the IRG</b></a> (Intergovernmental Referral Guide now available through the State Services Portal (SSP)) is located in the Interstate BPH.</li>\n<li>Refer to the <a href=\"?page_id=1587\"><b>ADVANCED INTERSTATE Q & A – APRIL ’07</b></a>, Caretaker (Interstate Cases) section for additional information on processing interstate caretaker cases.</li>\n</ol>\";}"
                     }
